en made implementing the recommendations of the report of the public inquiry into Mid Staffordshire NHS Foundation Trust.","false","Biography information for Heidi Alexander","Lewisham East","Heidi Alexander","39938"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523989","Department of Health","false","2016-06-14","<p>In 2014, NHS England published the <em>Five Year Forward View</em>, which included an account of five new care models designed to promote integrated service provision. 50 Vanguard sites are currently implementing a new care model, with the support of NHS England and the Department, and with a view to spreading lessons and best practice throughout the health system.</p><p>In order to deliver the best outcomes for service users, integration within the National Health Service must be accompanied by integration with social care. The Better Care Fund (BCF), first implemented in 2015/16, is continuing in 2016/17 and requires local government and the NHS to create pooled budgets in every area in England, bringing local leaders and clinical experts together to plan how to spend a portion of their shared resources to provide a more integrated health and care system for local people.</p><p>The BCF has laid the foundation for integration across the country, but the Government wants to go further, faster. The Autumn 2016 Spending Review set out the ambition that every area in England should integrate health and social care by 2020, with a plan for this in place by 2017. Achieving better integration within the NHS will be a key element of the broader ambition to integrate across the health and care system as a whole.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2016-06-14T11:54:03.667Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523989/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523989/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523989/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-06-08","Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps he is taking to promote integrated care in the NHS.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","39885"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523990","Department of Health","false","2016-06-16","<p>The Medicines and Healthcare products Regulatory Agency (MHRA) collects reports of suspected side effects to vaccines and medicines via the Yellow Card Scheme. It is important to note that a report of a suspected side effect does not necessarily mean the vaccine or medicine was the cause of the reported event, and coincidental illness can also be a factor. Such reports remain under continual review by the MHRA in order to detect possible new risks.</p><p> </p><p>The MHRA has received one suspected side effect report with a fatal outcome temporally associated with human papillomavirus (HPV) vaccine which occurred in the last three years. A link with the vaccine has not been established. There has been no suggestion from safety monitoring so far in the United Kingdom that the vaccine has been responsible for any deaths.</p><p> </p><p>More than three million girls have been vaccinated in the UK with HPV vaccine since 2008, and tens of millions more have been vaccinated globally. As with all vaccines, safety remains under continual review, and HPV vaccine has a very good safety record.</p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2016-06-16T09:17:29.56Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523990/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523990/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523990/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-06-08","Human Papillomavirus: Vaccination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many people under the age of 18 have died after receiving the HPV vaccination in the last three years.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","39887"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523991","Department of Health","false","2016-06-17","<p>No assessment has been made of the potential merits of providing laser-guided shoes to people with Parkinson's disease (PD) on the National Health Service. We understand this new innovation, whilst promising, remains at a relatively early stage in terms of development and testing. Good quality evidence from clinical trials would be needed before clinicians and commissioners could make appropriate assessments about the clinical and cost effectiveness of the shoes and consider their suitability for patients with PD.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-06-17T12:43:57.373Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523991/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523991/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523991/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-06-08","Parkinson's Disease","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of the potential merits of providing on the NHS laser-guided shoes to people with Parkinson's disease.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","39888"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523992","Department of Health","false","2016-06-14","<p>We are committed to ensuring that everyone at the end of life receives high quality, compassionate care that is tailored to their needs and preferences.</p><p>The Government will shortly publish its response to the independent Review of Choice in End of Life Care which will set out actions to improve quality, choice and personalisation of end of life care in the context of delivering the NHS Five Year Forward View throughout this Parliament.</p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer",,"2016-06-14T10:28:36.543Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523992/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523992/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523992/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-06-08","Palliative Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps he plans to take to improve end-of-life care over the next five years.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","39889"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523993","Department of Health","false","2016-06-15","<p>My Rt. hon. Friend the Secretary of State for Health has not had any such discussions.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-06-15T13:31:03.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523993/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523993/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523993/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-06-08","Obesity","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what recent discussions he has had with the Royal College of Nursing on the effect of boredom on obesity.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","39890"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523994","Home Office","false","2016-06-14","<p>The updated guidance on dealing with Family Reunion applications is currently being finalised and will shortly be available on GOV.UK at the following link:</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/asylum-decision-making-guidance-asylum-instructions</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2016-06-14T10:05:30.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523994/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523994/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523994/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-06-08","Asylum: Families","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, with reference to the Answer of 12 April 2016 to Question 32505, where the updated guidance on dealing with family reunion applications referred to in that Answer can be found.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","39877"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523995","Home Office","false","2016-06-13","<p>We are committed to monitoring the impact of the Psychoactive Substances Act 2016 which commenced on the 26 May.</p><p>Section 58 of the Act commits the Secretary of State to review the operation of the Act, prepare a report of the review, and lay a copy of the report before Parliament 30 months after the commencement of the Act. This review will therefore report its findings in late 2018.</p><p>Since commencement, the police have made arrests across the country of those involved in the supply of psychoactive substances; a number of head-shops have ceased trading and many more have handed in their remaining stock to be destroyed; and action by the National Crime Agency has resulted in the removal of psychoactive substances from sale by United Kingdom based websites.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2016-06-13T14:22:46.357Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523995/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523995/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523995/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-06-08","Drugs: Misuse","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps her Department is taking to monitor the effect of the introduction of the Psychoactive Substances Act 2016.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","39937"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523996","Home Office","false","2016-07-12","<p>The Authority to Carry Scheme 2015, made under sections 22 and 23 of the Counter-Terrorism and Security Act 2015, entered into force on 31 March 2015. Our records indicate that for each full month of its operation to date the number of individuals in respect of whom a carrier was refused authority to carry to the UK has been as follows:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Month/Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Number of individuals in respect of whom a carrier was refused authority to carry to the UK</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>April/15</p></td><td><p>67</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>May/15</p></td><td><p>56</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>June/15</p></td><td><p>77</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>July/15</p></td><td><p>77</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>August/15</p></td><td><p>80</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>September/15</p></td><td><p>90</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>October/15</p></td><td><p>106</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>November/15</p></td><td><p>92</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>December/15</p></td><td><p>89</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>January/16</p></td><td><p>69</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>February/16</p></td><td><p>61</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>March/16</p></td><td><p>79</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>April/16</p></td><td><p>82</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>May/16</p></td><td><p>107</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p><strong>Total: 1,132</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>This is provisional management information that is subject to change. It has not been assured to the standard of Official Statistics.</p><p>Individuals liable to be subject of a refusal of authority to carry include those who have been excluded from the UK, who have been deported from the UK and those who are using an invalid travel document such as a lost, stolen or cancelled passport.</p><p>The details of the Scheme are published at: www.gov.uk/government/publications/authority-to-carry-scheme-2015</p><p>The operation of the Scheme is just one part of the Government’s multi-layered approach to border security.</p><p>This includes the Home Secretary’s power to excluded individuals whose presence in the UK she considers is not conducive to the public good or is justified on public security grounds; a visa regime where applicants are subject to checks before a visa is issued and applications may be refused; guidance to airlines to help them decide who is incorrectly documented and should not travel to the UK and checks on all passengers arriving at the border on scheduled services which can result in refusal of entry to the UK.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2016-07-12T09:15:20.25Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523996/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523996/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523996/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-06-08","Travel Restrictions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many people were prevented from travelling to the UK by the authority to carry scheme in each month of its operation.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre  Brock","39971"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523997","Home Office","false","2016-06-14","<p>The Home Office has spent £860 million on the e-Borders and successor programmes since April 2006. Information prior to April 2006 is not available.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2016-06-14T10:05:41.55Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523997/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523997/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523997/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-06-08","Borders: Personal Records","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how much was spent on e-borders before April 2006; and how much has been spent on e-borders and its successor programmes since April 2006.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre  Brock","39972"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523998","Home Office","false","2016-06-13","<p>The Home Office has a unit processing Dublin III asylum transfer requests from and to the United Kingdom. This unit comprises 78.34 full time equivalent managers, caseworkers and support staff.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2016-06-13T17:22:14.317Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523998/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523998/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523998/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523998/answer/previousversion/3237","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523998/answer/previousversion/3237",,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-06-08","Asylum: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many full-time equivalent officials in her Department are responsible for identifying, verifying and processing potential Dublin Regulation transfer cases.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","39897"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523999","Home Office","false","2016-06-22","<p>The security of our border remains a absolute priority. Border Force works closely with domestic and international partners on an intelligence-led approach to identify unlawful maritime activity including facilitation and illegal entry.</p><p>Information on vessels travelling to and from the UK is collected from a range of sources and analysed at the National Maritime Information Centre. The Government keeps all options relating to advance notification requirements under review and will continue to ensure proportionate measures are in place to secure our border.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","39493","2016-06-22T10:31:21.71Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523999/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523999/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523999/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523999/answer/previousversion/3274","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523999/answer/previousversion/3274",,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-06-08","Immigration Controls: Shipping","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether she plans to introduce compulsory advanced notification for (a) commercial and (b) pleasure craft of arrival in the UK; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","40057"
