"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523363","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-06-13","<p>Post Office Limited runs and manages its directly managed Crown post offices. Changes to the Crown network and arrangements for employees of these offices are the operational responsibility of the Post Office.</p><p> </p><p>I have asked Paula Vennells, the Chief Executive of Post Office Limited, to write to the hon Member on this matter. A copy of her reply will be placed in the libraries of the House.</p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman","39589 ; 39590","2016-06-13T08:28:29.833Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523363/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523363/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523363/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-06-07","Post Office: Redundancy Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how much the Post Office has spent on settlement agreements and redundancy payments for Crown Office staff since January 2010.","false","Biography information for Mhairi Black","Paisley and Renfrewshire South","Mhairi Black","39588"
