"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523366","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-06-13","<p>I refer the hon Member to my response to question UIN <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=100&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;use-dates=True&amp;uin=39598" target="_blank">39342</a>.</p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-06-13T16:26:13.153Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523366/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523366/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523366/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-06-07","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills: Reorganisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, pursuant to the Written Statement of 26 May 2016, on BIS consultation, HCWS30, what assessment his Department has made of the relative level of difficulty in redeploying (a) London-based and (b) non-London-based staff to address urgent priorities.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","39598"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523367","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-06-14","<p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>The Department for Business, Innovation and Skills (BIS) is implementing its BIS2020 strategy in order to become simpler, cheaper and better. This includes moving to a central policy headquarters based in London.</p><p> </p><p>An assessment was made of the merits of split site working and of recruiting on a flexible basis through the consideration of alternative options (including maintaining the current model across split sites). This assessment took place throughout the consultation process and prior to the Executive Board’s decision.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>BIS will continue to have many more people based outside London than inside.</p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-06-14T09:00:30.163Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523367/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523367/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523367/answer","Orpington","Joseph Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523367/answer/previousversion/3429","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523367/answer/previousversion/3429",,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-06-07","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills: Reorganisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, pursuant to the Written Statement of 26 May 2016, on BIS consultation, HCWS30, what assessment he has made of the potential merits of split-site working and recruiting on a flexible location basis for policy officials.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","39599"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523368","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-06-10","<p>As at 31 May 2016 the number of employees of the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills, working in the Sheffield office at St Paul's Place at (a) Senior Civil Service level and (b) below Senior Civil Service level, are shown in the table below.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Grade</p></td><td><p>Employees</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Senior Civil Service level</p></td><td><p>8</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Below Senior Civil Service level</p></td><td><p>214</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-06-10T10:44:37.593Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523368/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523368/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523368/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-06-07","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills: Sheffield","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, with reference to the Written Statement of 26 May 2016, HCWS30, how many roles there are (a) at and (b) below Senior Civil Service level based in the Sheffield office at St Paul's Place.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","39618"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523369","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-06-14","<p>There is already consumer protection legislation in place that protects consumers when dealing with traders, including car hire firms. The Consumer Protection from Unfair Trading Regulations 2008 (CPRs) prohibit traders from engaging in unfair commercial practices, such as providing false or deceptive information or descriptions to consumers or leaving out material information.</p><p> </p><p>Local authority trading standards services and the Competition and Markets Authority enforce the CPRs, and breaches of the legislation can be reported to the Citizens Advice consumer helpline on 03454 04 05 06 in the first instance.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, the Consumer Contracts (Information, Cancellation and Additional Charges) Regulations 2013 (CCRs) require traders entering into distance and online contracts to provide consumers with a range of pre-purchase information in a clear and comprehensive manner, including any additional costs and how they will be calculated.</p><p> </p><p>Finally, the Consumer Rights Act 2015 (CRA) provides a wide range of protections for consumers, including restricting the use of unfair terms in consumer contracts. Under the CRA, an ‘unfair term’ is defined as one which, contrary to the requirements of good faith, causes a significant imbalance in the parties’ rights and obligations under the contract to the detriment of the consumer. If a court decides a term is unfair, it will not be binding on the consumer.</p><p> </p><p>A term, such as the price and the main subject matter, may be exempted from the assessment of fairness if it is transparent and prominent (expressed in plain and intelligible language and legible) and brought to the consumer’s attention in such a way as the average consumer would be aware of it.</p><p> </p><p>The consumer protection legislation referred to implements EU legislation which applies in all other member states.</p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-06-14T13:02:38.813Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523369/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523369/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523369/answer","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523369/answer/previousversion/3431","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523369/answer/previousversion/3431",,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-06-07","Cars: Hire Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what steps he is taking to (a) improve the transparency of car hire firms and (b) ensure people hiring cars are not incorrectly charged for damage to such cars.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","39638"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523370","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-06-14","<p>Detailed planning within business areas is continuing in order to assess for which roles there is a permanent business need, and which are either no longer needed or only needed in the short term.</p><p>Based on current estimates the Department expects less than half of the policy roles currently outside London to transfer and be backfilled permanently, as part of the overall reduction in policy roles from 2000 to 1500.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-06-14T15:34:14.323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523370/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523370/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523370/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-06-07","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills: Reorganisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, with reference to the Written Statement of 26 May 2016, HCWS30, what assessment he has made of the business need for the roles based at (a) the Sheffield office at St Paul's Place and (b) the London office at 1 Victoria Street.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","39619"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523371","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-06-16","<p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>Co-locating policy teams with the Department’s Ministers and close to Parliament will provide opportunities for all staff to have more ministerial exposure, which helps improve understanding of government priorities.</p><p> </p><p>The Department does not expect a set number of roles to be consistently exposed to Ministers whilst others are not. This will be dynamic as resource demands shift over time and will depend on policy priorities.</p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-06-16T10:24:55.977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523371/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523371/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523371/answer","Orpington","Joseph Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523371/answer/previousversion/3437","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523371/answer/previousversion/3437",,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-06-07","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills: Reorganisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, with reference to the Written Statement of 26 May 2016, HCWS30, what proportion of the 1,500 roles will have ministerial exposure following the centralisation of policy functions in London.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","39631"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523372","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-06-15","<p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>The Department has estimated that the transition costs associated with creating a combined policy centre and headquarters in London will be in the range of £9-13m which would be recouped in savings by the end of the Parliament. This model will better enable the Department to operate a more flexible, agile and easily re-deployable policy function which will continue to deliver BIS’ priorities as it reduces in size over the course of the Parliament.</p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-06-15T14:44:02.533Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523372/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523372/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523372/answer","Orpington","Joseph Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523372/answer/previousversion/3442","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523372/answer/previousversion/3442",,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-06-07","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills: Reorganisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, with reference to the Written Statement of 26 May 2016, HCWS30, what estimate he has made of the transition costs associated with the decision to create a combined Business, Innovation and Skills headquarters and policy function in London.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","39632"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523373","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-06-13","<p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>Details of Ministerial meetings are published quarterly alongside gifts, hospitality and travel on the GOV.UK website.</p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-06-13T10:05:36.14Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523373/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523373/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523373/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-06-07","Mark Samworth","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, whether he has met Mark Samworth, owner of the food manufacturing company Samworths, in the last six months.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","39669"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523374","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-06-15","<p>The Department for Business, Innovation and Skills is developing a Resourcing Strategy that will include targeted recruitment over the next few years including apprenticeships, graduate recruitment, loans from other Government Departments and increasing the use of secondments from the private sector. These interventions, along with having clear workforce plans across the organisation, including undertaking more internal managed moves to deliver priority work, will help reduce the Department’s vacancy rate.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-06-15T16:48:28.09Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523374/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523374/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523374/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-06-07","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills: Vacancies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what steps he is taking to reduce his Department's vacancy rate.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","39715"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523375","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-06-15","<p>We are developing the digital apprenticeship service to support apprenticeships in England. It will help all employers to select an apprenticeship framework or standard, choose a training provider, choose an assessment organisation and post apprenticeship vacancies. By 2020, all employers will be able to use the service to pay for training and assessment for apprenticeships and we will help smaller employers to prepare for this.</p><p>We continue to work with a wide range of employers to develop, test and improve the digital apprenticeship service.</p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-06-15T14:20:52.91Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523375/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523375/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523375/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-06-07","Small Businesses: Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what steps he plans to take to involve small and medium-sized enterprises in the proposed digital apprenticeship system.","false","Biography information for Neil Coyle","Bermondsey and Old Southwark","Neil Coyle","39704"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523376","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-06-15","<p>The United Kingdom, through the UK Space Agency (UKSA), is one of the thirteen members of the Inter-Agency Debris Coordination (IADC) Committee, which considers the risks posed by space debris. Our national experts, along with more than a hundred experts from other agencies including NASA, met at Harwell in March 2016 for the annual IADC meeting to discuss many issues, including the need for the removal of space debris from orbit, and how that could best be accomplished.</p><p>The UK is leading studies in partnership with other national agencies to model the future space environment and identify the most effective ways of mitigating the future hazard of space debris.</p><p>UKSA is working with its international partners in technical forums such as the IADC to develop scientific consensus on the best way to manage the hazard posed by debris, such as how many objects might need to be removed, and from where. UKSA is also working to build political consensus within UN forums such as the Committee on the Peaceful Uses of Outer Space to enable such missions to go ahead with appropriate supervision and support from the international community. This includes developing appropriate regulatory/oversight frameworks within the UK’s Outer Space Act which allow such technologies to be tested and demonstrated safely in the increasingly congested and contested space environment.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-06-15T16:57:40.107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523376/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523376/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523376/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-06-07","Space Debris","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what steps the Government is taking to promote action to remove space debris.","false","Biography information for Adam Afriyie","Windsor","Adam Afriyie","39726"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523377","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-06-14","<p>The Government is committed to making the UK one of the safest places in the world to do business online and we recognise the role cyber insurance can play as part of a broader risk management strategy.</p><p>In March 2015 the Government published a report on the joint initiatives between Government and the insurance sector to tackle cyber risk. The report is available here:<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/news/cyber-security-insurance-new-steps-to-make-uk-world-centre" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/news/cyber-security-insurance-new-steps-to-make-uk-world-centre</a></p><p> </p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2016-06-14T10:49:07.043Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523377/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523377/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523377/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-06-07","Cybercrime: Insurance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps he is taking to support and spread awareness of cyber security insurance amongst businesses.","false","Biography information for Adam Afriyie","Windsor","Adam Afriyie","39727"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523378","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-06-15","<p>The Department for Business, Innovation and Skills (BIS) recognises the interest in its decision to establish a combined headquarters and policy centre in London, which is why a summary of the decision and its rationale was issued on BIS’ website, and why a Written Ministerial Statement was laid informing all MPs on the day of the decision.</p><p>The document was written specifically with staff in mind as a piece of internal communications and as a response to the staff consultation BIS conducted. The Department’s top priority is ensuring staff have the most up to date and accurate information about the support available to them. We have no plans to publish the document because it contains information on issues which are the subject of on-going internal discussions with staff.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-06-15T11:35:50.78Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523378/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523378/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523378/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-06-07","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills: Reorganisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, if he will publish his Department's consultation response on the proposal for a combined headquarters and policy centre in London.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","39823"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523379","HM Treasury","false","2016-06-15","<p>EU science, education and research schemes are awarded on the basis of excellence and are not pre-allocated. As a world leader in these sectors, the UK has a strong track record at securing these funds – in recent years around 15% of such receipts from Horizon 2020, the EU’s main research programme, have gone to the UK. The deal secured by the Government on the 2014-2020 Multiannual Financial Framework (MFF) resulted in an increase of over one third in the proportion of the EU budget spent on competitiveness, research, innovation and university funding. In addition, Horizon 2020’s budget was almost 30% higher in real terms than its predecessor programme. The post-2020 MFF has not been proposed.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-06-15T14:36:06.417Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523379/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523379/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523379/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-06-07","EU Grants and Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will estimate the amount of funding that will be made available to each part of the UK for science, education and research purposes through EU schemes in the post-2020 Multiannual Financial Framework.","false","Biography information for Karl McCartney","Lincoln","Karl McCartney","39803"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523380","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-06-15","<p>Details of Ministerial meetings are published quarterly on <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/bis-quarterly-publications-april-to-june-2012" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/bis-quarterly-publications-april-to-june-2012</a>, including meetings as part of official visits in Scotland.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-06-15T16:58:41.443Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523380/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523380/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523380/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-06-07","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many times he has visited Scotland in an official capacity since the 2015 General Election; and what meetings were held on each such visit.","false","Biography information for Chris Law","Dundee West","Chris Law","39827"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523381","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-06-14","<p>No decision on the future of Land Registry has been taken and as such, no bids have been received. The consultation on moving operations of Land Registry to the private sector closed on 26 May and Government are currently reviewing the responses. Until this is completed, no decision will be made.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-06-14T11:46:49.203Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523381/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523381/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523381/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-06-07","Land Registry: Privatisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, whether account is being taken in the proposed sale of the Land Registry of whether interested bidders are based in tax havens; what assessment his Department made in the awarding of such contracts of the competitive advantage given to companies based in tax havens; and what recent discussions he has had with his Ministerial colleagues on banning companies based in tax havens from purchasing assets sold during privatisations.","false","Biography information for Stephen Kinnock","Aberavon","Stephen Kinnock","39816"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523382","Cabinet Office","false","2016-06-10","<p>Statistics in relation to Freedom of information requests are publically available on gov.uk at https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-06-10T13:15:53.253Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523382/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523382/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523382/answer",,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-06-07","Cabinet Office: Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many Freedom of Information requests have been refused by his Department in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","39724"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523383","Cabinet Office","false","2016-06-10","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave to him on 11 March 2016 to UIN: 29744.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-06-10T13:17:58.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523383/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523383/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523383/answer",,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-06-07","Regulation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many officials of his Department have specific policy responsibility for deregulation.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","39723"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523384","Cabinet Office","false","2016-06-14","<p>This Government has taken a number of steps to ensure effective whistleblowing practices are in place across Departments and to raise the profile and awareness of whilstleblowing. Updated and refreshed model whistleblowing policies are in place across all departments, providing information on sources of support available to whistleblowers, including access to employee assistance programmes, and advice on accessing legal support. In addition, we have improved support for Nominated Offices, and Departments have introduced dedicated whistleblowing hotlines and are publishing case studies on departmental intranet sites to build confidence that cases will be heard fairly and appropriately.</p><p>The Cabinet Office has developed a new data collection tool to enable HR Directors to collect information on whistleblowing cases including how cases have been resolved, identification of systemic issues, and lessons learned. Departments are using this tool to report to their Departmental Boards, and to the Cabinet Office, on a 6 monthly basis.</p><p>More details on action taken by specific Departments, including the first set of data collated by Departments, can be found in the Cabinet Office’s recent report to the Public Accounts Committee: <a href="http://data.parliament.uk/writtenevidence/committeeevidence.svc/evidencedocument/public-accounts-committee/whistleblowing-recall/written/31692.html" target="_blank">http://data.parliament.uk/writtenevidence/committeeevidence.svc/evidencedocument/public-accounts-committee/whistleblowing-recall/written/31692.html</a></p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","39719","2016-06-14T08:52:12.897Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523384/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523384/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523384/answer",,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-06-07","Cabinet Office: Disclosure of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what steps he is taking to promote a whistleblowing culture in his Department.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","39720"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523385","Cabinet Office","false","2016-06-15","<p>The Government is making good progress and will publish draft legislation in due course.</p>","Weston-super-Mare","John Penrose",,"2016-06-15T09:43:42.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523385/answer","Biography information for John Penrose","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523385/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523385/answer",,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-06-07","Public Sector: Ombudsman","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what progress he has made on bringing forward proposals for a modern public services ombudsman in the last three months.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","39718"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523386","Cabinet Office","false","2016-06-14","<p>The Government is committed to increasing the diversity of public appointments and​ has an​ aspiration that 50% of new public appointees should be women. We are making ​good ​progress, with 44% of new appointments made to women in 2014-2015, up from 39% the previous year. For many years, the figure on appointments was between 32-36%, 44% is the highest figure since records began.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-06-14T08:53:18.24Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523386/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523386/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523386/answer",,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-06-07","Public Appointments: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what proportion of people appointed to public bodies are women.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","39721"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523387","Cabinet Office","false","2016-06-14","<p>This Government has taken a number of steps to ensure effective whistleblowing practices are in place across Departments and to raise the profile and awareness of whilstleblowing. Updated and refreshed model whistleblowing policies are in place across all departments, providing information on sources of support available to whistleblowers, including access to employee assistance programmes, and advice on accessing legal support. In addition, we have improved support for Nominated Offices, and Departments have introduced dedicated whistleblowing hotlines and are publishing case studies on departmental intranet sites to build confidence that cases will be heard fairly and appropriately.</p><p>The Cabinet Office has developed a new data collection tool to enable HR Directors to collect information on whistleblowing cases including how cases have been resolved, identification of systemic issues, and lessons learned. Departments are using this tool to report to their Departmental Boards, and to the Cabinet Office, on a 6 monthly basis.</p><p>More details on action taken by specific Departments, including the first set of data collated by Departments, can be found in the Cabinet Office’s recent report to the Public Accounts Committee: <a href="http://data.parliament.uk/writtenevidence/committeeevidence.svc/evidencedocument/public-accounts-committee/whistleblowing-recall/written/31692.html" target="_blank">http://data.parliament.uk/writtenevidence/committeeevidence.svc/evidencedocument/public-accounts-committee/whistleblowing-recall/written/31692.html</a></p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","39720","2016-06-14T08:52:12.833Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523387/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523387/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523387/answer",,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-06-07","Civil Servants: Disclosure of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what steps he is taking to promote a whistleblowing culture across the civil service.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","39719"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523388","Cabinet Office","false","2016-06-14","<p>The Anti-Corruption Innovation Hub is a virtual network which brings together government, civil society, law enforcement, technologists and the private sector to share cross-sector expertise and new ideas on how to tackle corruption.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-06-14T08:59:54.48Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523388/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523388/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523388/answer",,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-06-07","Anti-corruption Innovation Hub","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what the terms of reference are for the new Anti-corruption Innovation Hub.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","39683"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523389","Cabinet Office","false","2016-06-14","<p>There will be a full time member of staff with additional support as part of joint commitment between the Government and Omidyar Network.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-06-14T09:00:39.42Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523389/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523389/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523389/answer",,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-06-07","Anti-corruption Innovation Hub","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many members of staff will be recruited to form the Anti-corruption Innovation Hub.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","39682"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523390","Cabinet Office","false","2016-06-14","<p>Building on the UK's Anti Corruption Plan and the Prime Minister's successful summit, the UK has committed to develop a new national anti-corruption strategy which will provide a vision and framework for our domestic and international policy priorities. We are reviewing the governance arrangements for the strategy and will announce them in due course.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-06-14T08:59:01.703Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523390/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523390/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523390/answer",,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-06-07","Anti-corruption Innovation Hub","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, which Government Minister will have responsibility for overseeing the implementation of the new anti-corruption strategy.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","39684"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523391","Cabinet Office","false","2016-06-16","<p>The total expenditure of the Commission on Freedom of Information was £155,744.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-06-16T14:51:09.903Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523391/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523391/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523391/answer","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523391/answer/previousversion/3382","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523391/answer/previousversion/3382",,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-06-07","Commission on Freedom of Information: Costs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, with reference to the Answer of 9 March 2016 to Question 29669, what progress he has made on establishing the cost to the public purse of the Independent Commission on Freedom of Information.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","39672"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523392","Cabinet Office","false","2016-06-10","<p>The information requested is not held.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-06-10T13:20:21.657Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523392/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523392/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523392/answer",,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-06-07","Cabinet Office: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many officials in his Department have applied for special leave to carry out work for non-governmental departments in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","39680"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523393","Cabinet Office","false","2016-06-14","<p>For the 12 month period between 8/6/15 and 7/6/16, Cabinet Office advertised 26 vacancies for internal applicants on its intranet site. In the same period, 469 Cabinet Office vacancies were advertised on the Civil Service Jobs search internet page.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-06-14T08:56:29.663Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523393/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523393/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523393/answer",,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-06-07","Cabinet Office: Vacancies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many job vacancies in his Department have been reserved as internal posts in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","39681"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523394","Cabinet Office","false","2016-06-14","<p>The Centre for Public Appointments in the Cabinet Office supports departments on all issues relating to the diversity of public appointments. Steps we are taking to increase diversity include streamlining the application process​, placing an emphasis on ability over previous experience,​ and increasing awareness of opportunities by using a central website and social media.</p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-06-14T08:55:43.867Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523394/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523394/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523394/answer","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523394/answer/previousversion/3373","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523394/answer/previousversion/3373",,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-06-07","Public Appointments: Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what steps he is taking to increase diversity in public appointments.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","39603"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523395","HM Treasury","false","2016-06-13","<p>The government is committed to launching a retail sale of Lloyds Banking Group shares and to fully returning its stake to the private sector in 2016-17.</p><p> </p><p>Those applying to invest less than £1,000 will be prioritised. Members of the public will be offered a discount on the market price and, to encourage long term share ownership, investors who hold their shares for more than a year will be entitled to bonus shares.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-06-13T15:09:33.933Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523395/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523395/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523395/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-06-07","Lloyds Banking Group: Government Shareholding","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, when he plans to launch the next Lloyds Bank share offer; and what incentives he plans to include in that offer to encourage small shareholders to retain shares that they purchase.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","39642"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523396","HM Treasury","false","2016-06-13","<p>Each year HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) carry out rigorous assurance testing of the annual issue of tax codes to ensure a high level of accuracy. For 2016-17 the accuracy of annual PAYE coding notices, (based on information that HMRC receives during the year), is around 99 per cent.</p><p>HMRC have developed the new online Personal Tax Account which gives customers the ability to review their own personal tax status and encourages them to keep HMRC updated on changes in their personal circumstances to ensure even more customers are paying the correct tax at the right time.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-06-13T14:11:01.29Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523396/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523396/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523396/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-06-07","Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what steps he is taking to ensure people are not assigned incorrect tax codes.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","39639"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523397","HM Treasury","false","2016-06-13","<p>This government is committed to ensuring that older people are able to live with the dignity and respect they deserve and the State Pension is the foundation of state support for older people. That is why the government has committed to increasing the State Pension by the triple lock, with someone on a full basic State Pension receiving around £570 more in 2016-17 than if it had been uprated by average earnings since the start of the last Parliament.</p><p> </p><p>In total, the government will spend around £95 billion on the State Pension in 2016-17.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-06-13T15:13:23.57Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523397/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523397/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523397/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-06-07","Older People: Payments","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will introduce a payment of £1,000 to each person reaching the age of 100.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","39641"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523398","Department for Transport","false","2016-06-14","<p>The Government has made no such estimate and does not have comprehensive data on how airlines adjusted their schedules during the strikes, or the impacts on passengers.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-06-14T08:59:10.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523398/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523398/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523398/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-07","Air Traffic Control: Strikes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will estimate the cost to the EU economy of strikes by air traffic controllers across Europe in 2014 and 2015.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","39708"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523399","HM Treasury","false","2016-06-13","<p>We have not received any unpublished EU budget proposals or any re-assessments and adjustments relating to EU budgets of previous years. Any budget proposals must conform to the legally binding annual expenditure ceilings agreed in the Multiannual Financial Framework 2014-2020.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-06-13T15:33:52.703Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523399/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523399/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523399/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-06-07","EU Budget","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether he has seen the latest draft of the EU Commission's proposals for the (a) EU Budget and (b) any re-assessment and adjustments relating to previous years budgets; and if he will publish those proposals and their effect on the public purse before 23 June 2016.","false","Biography information for Karl McCartney","Lincoln","Karl McCartney","39777"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523400","HM Treasury","false","2016-06-13","<p>Treasury Ministers and officials have meetings with a wide variety of organisations in the public and private sectors as part of the process of policy development and delivery. Details of ministerial and permanent secretary meetings with external organisations on departmental business are published on a quarterly basis and are available at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/hmt-ministers-meetings-hospitality-gifts-and-overseas-travel" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/hmt-ministers-meetings-hospitality-gifts-and-overseas-travel</a></p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-06-13T10:32:53.39Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523400/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523400/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523400/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-06-07","Mark Samworth","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether he has met with Mr Mark Samworth in the last six months.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","39782"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523401","HM Treasury","false","2016-06-13","<p>Treasury Ministers regularly visit all parts of the United Kingdom as part of their official duties.</p><p> </p><p>Details of ministerial and permanent secretary meetings with external organisations on departmental business are published on a quarterly basis and are available at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/hmt-ministers-meetings-hospitality-gifts-and-overseas-travel" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/hmt-ministers-meetings-hospitality-gifts-and-overseas-travel</a></p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-06-13T13:53:45.593Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523401/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523401/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523401/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-06-07","Treasury: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many times he has visited Scotland in an official capacity since the 2015 General Election; and what meetings were held on each such visit.","false","Biography information for Chris Law","Dundee West","Chris Law","39841"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523402","HM Treasury","false","2016-06-15","<p>The Government seeks to ensure value for money for the taxpayer in conducting asset sales. This includes running sales on a competitive basis that are open to a wide range of potential buyers. The Government has no plans to change the existing arrangements governing participation in the sale of government assets.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-06-15T14:37:30.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523402/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523402/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523402/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-06-07","Tax Havens","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will introduce measures to prevent companies based in tax havens from purchasing assets during privatisations.","false","Biography information for Stephen Kinnock","Aberavon","Stephen Kinnock","39770"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523403","HM Treasury","false","2016-06-15","<p>The UK regularly reviews its treaty network and actively engages with developing countries. Discussions with Malawi over a new tax treaty began some years ago, and substantive agreement has been reached at official level. It is hoped that the treaty will be signed shortly. Although the UK’s starting point in negotiations is based closely on the OECD model double taxation convention, the Government recognises that developing countries will sometimes have different preferences, and treaties the UK has recently signed demonstrate that we are willing to accommodate at least some of those preferences as part of a balanced agreement. But the nature of the negotiating process is that it remains confidential to the two sides until the treaty is signed.</p><p> </p><p>By governing the taxation of cross-border income flows in a predictable manner and eliminating double taxation and excessive taxation, tax treaties promote international trade and investment, leading to sustainable tax revenues, which are vital in financing for development.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","39861 ; 39862","2016-06-15T15:24:25.993Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523403/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523403/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523403/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-06-07","Taxation: Malawi","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will take steps to ensure that the renegotiation of the UK-Malawi tax treaty supports development and helps tackle poverty in that country.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","39860"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523404","HM Treasury","false","2016-06-15","<p>The UK regularly reviews its treaty network and actively engages with developing countries. Discussions with Malawi over a new tax treaty began some years ago, and substantive agreement has been reached at official level. It is hoped that the treaty will be signed shortly. Although the UK’s starting point in negotiations is based closely on the OECD model double taxation convention, the Government recognises that developing countries will sometimes have different preferences, and treaties the UK has recently signed demonstrate that we are willing to accommodate at least some of those preferences as part of a balanced agreement. But the nature of the negotiating process is that it remains confidential to the two sides until the treaty is signed.</p><p> </p><p>By governing the taxation of cross-border income flows in a predictable manner and eliminating double taxation and excessive taxation, tax treaties promote international trade and investment, leading to sustainable tax revenues, which are vital in financing for development.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","39860 ; 39862","2016-06-15T15:24:26.07Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523404/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523404/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523404/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-06-07","Taxation: Treaties","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will take steps to improve the transparency of the negotiation process for UK tax treaties.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","39861"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523405","HM Treasury","false","2016-06-15","<p>The UK regularly reviews its treaty network and actively engages with developing countries. Discussions with Malawi over a new tax treaty began some years ago, and substantive agreement has been reached at official level. It is hoped that the treaty will be signed shortly. Although the UK’s starting point in negotiations is based closely on the OECD model double taxation convention, the Government recognises that developing countries will sometimes have different preferences, and treaties the UK has recently signed demonstrate that we are willing to accommodate at least some of those preferences as part of a balanced agreement. But the nature of the negotiating process is that it remains confidential to the two sides until the treaty is signed.</p><p> </p><p>By governing the taxation of cross-border income flows in a predictable manner and eliminating double taxation and excessive taxation, tax treaties promote international trade and investment, leading to sustainable tax revenues, which are vital in financing for development.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","39860 ; 39861","2016-06-15T15:24:26.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523405/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523405/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523405/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-06-07","Taxation: Developing Countries","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will make an assessment of the effect of the UK's tax treaties with developing countries on tackling poverty in those countries.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","39862"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523406","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-06-13","<p>Decentralisation and growth are cross-governmental issues, supported by officials in all relevant departments.</p><p>The Cities and Local Growth Unit is a joint BIS-DCLG team that supports areas in developing and agreeing devolution deals with the Government. It currently has approximately 140 officials working on a range of devolution and growth agendas, with just over 60 of these officials in six local teams based across the country.</p><p> </p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2016-06-13T15:35:21.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523406/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523406/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523406/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-06-07","Department for Communities and Local Government: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what proportion of officials of his Department working on decentralisation and growth are based in London.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","39850"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523407","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-06-13","<p>The Department has not made an estimate of the historic demand on housing caused by inward migration in each of the last 10 years.</p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2016-06-13T15:31:51.67Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523407/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523407/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523407/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-06-07","Housing: Immigrants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will estimate the increase in demand on housing caused by inward migration in each of the last 10 years for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Karl McCartney","Lincoln","Karl McCartney","39851"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523408","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-06-13","<p>Raw data from the English Housing Survey are publicly available via the UK Data Service (archive for survey and economic data). These publicly available datasets undergo rigorous disclosure control to ensure the anonymity of our respondents is protected and, as such, do not include individual level nationality data.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2016-06-13T15:46:34.22Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523408/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523408/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523408/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-06-07","Households: Nationality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will place in the Library the raw data from each English Housing Survey detailing the nationalities of the Household Representative Person.","false","Biography information for Karl McCartney","Lincoln","Karl McCartney","39852"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523409","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-06-15","<p>Whilst the Secretary of State has not visited Scotland since the 2015 General Election, officials have had a number of meetings on proposed City Deals across Scotland.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2016-06-15T15:33:43.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523409/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523409/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523409/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-06-07","Department for Communities and Local Government: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many times he has visited Scotland since the 2015 General Election; and what meetings, with whom, were held on each of those visits.","false","Biography information for Chris Law","Dundee West","Chris Law","39824"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523410","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-06-14","<p>On 17 April 2014, the former Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, the Rt Hon Vince Cable MP, set out the methodology for how the UK's Structural Funds were to be allocated in his letter ‘European Regional Development Fund and European Social Fund: UK allocations 2014 to 2020’.</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/307492/bis-14-772-uk-allocations-eu-structural-funds-2014-2020-letter.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/307492/bis-14-772-uk-allocations-eu-structural-funds-2014-2020-letter.pdf</a></p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2016-06-14T14:49:26.143Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523410/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523410/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523410/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-06-07","EU Grants and Loans: Cornwall","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what change there was in the amount the EU Commission proposed to make available in structural funds to Cornwall for the period 2014-2020 and the period 2007-2013; and what steps his Department took to limit such changes.","false","Biography information for Karl McCartney","Lincoln","Karl McCartney","39793"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523411","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-06-14","<p>The post-2020 Multiannual Financial Framework has not been proposed.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton","39810","2016-06-14T14:50:38.207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523411/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523411/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523411/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-06-07","EU Grants and Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will estimate the level of structural funding that the EU Commission will allocate to each region in England in the post-2020 Multiannual Financial Framework.","false","Biography information for Karl McCartney","Lincoln","Karl McCartney","39805"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523412","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-06-14","<p>The post-2020 Multiannual Financial Framework has not been proposed.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton","39805","2016-06-14T14:50:38.27Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523412/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523412/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523412/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-06-07","EU Grants and Loans: Cornwall","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will estimate the level of structural funding that the EU Commission will allocate to Cornwall in the post-2020 Multiannual Financial Framework.","false","Biography information for Karl McCartney","Lincoln","Karl McCartney","39810"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523413","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-06-13","<p>I would welcome a proactive and enthusiastic approach to involvement on devolution matters and associated opportunities locally, with which my department stands ready to engage. It is for hon. Members to determine for themselves what that involves.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2016-06-13T15:38:21.353Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523413/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523413/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523413/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-06-07","Local Government: Devolution","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, with reference to the Answer of 9 May 2016 to Question 36419, if he will set out the actions required of an hon. Member, including the number of parliamentary questions asked, contributions to debate and other relevant matters which are deemed to demonstrate sufficient interest in devolution, for such hon. Members to be invited to meetings on future plans for the area they represent.","false","Biography information for Helen Jones","Warrington North","Helen Jones","39855"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523414","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-06-13","<p>The department collects details on the nationality of all household reference persons in the English Housing Survey. However, the sample size of the English Housing Survey does not permit us to report detailed nationality statistics.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2016-06-13T15:47:04.137Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523414/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523414/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523414/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-06-07","Housing: Foreign Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will estimate the total number and proportion of dwellings in the UK occupied with the Households Representative Person being a foreign national from (a) another EU member state and (b) a non-EU country in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Karl McCartney","Lincoln","Karl McCartney","39854"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523415","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-06-13","<p>The Department has not made an estimate of the additional new housing needed to provide accommodation for immigrants from EU and non-EU countries.</p><p>Housing needs are assessed by local authorities based on local need, and Government does not set figures.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2016-06-13T15:56:26.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523415/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523415/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523415/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-06-07","Housing: Immigrants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will estimate the additional new housing required to address demand caused by immigration from (a) other EU member states and (b) non-EU member states in each year to 2030.","false","Biography information for Karl McCartney","Lincoln","Karl McCartney","39853"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523416","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-06-15","<p>The department collects details on the nationality of all household reference persons in the English Housing Survey. However, the sample size of the English Housing Survey does not permit us to report detailed nationality statistics.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2016-06-15T15:32:33.79Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523416/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523416/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523416/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-06-07","Households: Nationality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, for what reasons the English Housing Survey Headline Report 2014 to 2015, published in February 2016, did not contain a breakdown of the nationality of the Households Representative Person by tenure; and if he will publish the data held on the nationality of the Households Representative Person by tenure for each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Karl McCartney","Lincoln","Karl McCartney","39706"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523417","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-06-14","<p>The biannual Traveller Caravan Count includes figures for the number of traveller caravans on unauthorised encampments in each local authority area in England.</p><p>The figures for the January and July 2015 counts can be found via the following links:</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/traveller-caravan-count-january-2015</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/traveller-caravan-count-july-2015</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2016-06-14T14:57:07.94Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523417/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523417/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523417/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-06-07","Travellers: Caravan Sites","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many unauthorised encampments were recorded in each county and metropolitan borough in 2015 in England.","false","Biography information for Wendy Morton","Aldridge-Brownhills","Wendy Morton","39620"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523419","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-06-14","<p>We regularly receive correspondence from individual local authorities and MPs, concerning the powers available to enforcement agencies and operation of the planning system. The Government takes the issue of unauthorised encampments and associated problems seriously and will continue to keep it under review.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2016-06-14T14:55:56.683Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523419/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523419/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523419/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-06-07","Travellers: Caravan Sites","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what representations his Department has received from each (a) local authority, (b) Police and Crime Commissioner and (c) Police Chief Constable seeking further powers in relation to responsibilities to stop unauthorised encampments in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Wendy Morton","Aldridge-Brownhills","Wendy Morton","39622"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523420","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-06-13","<p>Information for 2014-15 is available in tables RO3 (Social care and Public Health) and RS (Revenue Summary) available here:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/local-authority-revenue-expenditure-and-financing-england-2014-to-2015-individual-local-authority-data-outturn" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/local-authority-revenue-expenditure-and-financing-england-2014-to-2015-individual-local-authority-data-outturn<br></a><br>Local authorities receive a ring-fenced public health grant from the Department for Health but physical activity is a non-prescribed public health function. Local authorities are best placed to assess and deliver the services their communities need and are locally accountable for those decisions, therefore this spending has not been formally analysed by the department.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","39635","2016-06-13T15:39:46.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523420/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523420/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523420/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-06-07","Exercise","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what assessment his Department has made of the variation in spending by each local authority on physical activity services per capita.","false","Biography information for Liz McInnes","Heywood and Middleton","Liz McInnes","39636"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523421","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-06-13","<p>The information requested is not held centrally.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2016-06-13T15:44:14.32Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523421/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523421/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523421/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-06-07","Housing Associations: Demolition","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many housing associations have demolished residential buildings that are less than 10 years old in each of the last five years; and what the reasons were for those demolitions.","false","Biography information for Ms Harriet Harman","Camberwell and Peckham","Ms Harriet Harman","39607"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523422","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-06-13","<p>None. The Regulator is aware of the issues relating to Solomon’s Passage in Peckham. They are currently considering the information provided by Wandle Housing Association in line with our processes for dealing with referrals related to the consumer standards.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2016-06-13T15:42:11.83Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523422/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523422/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523422/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-06-07","Demolition: Greater London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what recent discussions he has had with (a) the Homes and Communities Agency and (b) Wandle Housing Association Limited on the demolition of residential buildings in Solomon's Passage, Peckham.","false","Biography information for Ms Harriet Harman","Camberwell and Peckham","Ms Harriet Harman","39608"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523423","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-06-15","<p>Civil Service Learning, the main training portal for civil servants, has a broad range of diversity and inclusion learning, which is available to all civil servants. There is also a two day course covering both Abrahamic and Dharmic religions for officials who need a more in depth understanding to carry out their role.</p><p>DCLG officials have had discussions with the Commission on Religion and Belief in Public Life (CORAB) about their call for greater religious literacy in every section of society. The Government is aware of the recent evidence sessions on religious literacy held by the All Party Parliamentary Group on Religious Education and will carefully consider the findings of the Group's report when it is published.</p><p /><p><em><p><p></em></p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2016-06-15T16:54:35.35Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523423/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523423/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523423/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-06-07","Department for Communities and Local Government: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will take steps to ensure that staff in his Department receive religious literacy training.","false","Biography information for Fiona Bruce","Congleton","Fiona Bruce","39675"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523424","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-06-14","<p>My Department is considering a number of issues related to the Building Regulations and building control system matters. We will make an announcement about our plans in due course.</p><p> </p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2016-06-14T14:52:32.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523424/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523424/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523424/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-06-07","Building Regulations: Fires","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what plans he has to review the guidance provided in Approved Document B to the Building Regulations 2010.","false","Biography information for Lyn Brown","West Ham","Lyn Brown","39625"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523425","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-06-13","<p>Information for 2014-15 is available in tables RO3 (Social care and Public Health) and RS (Revenue Summary) available here:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/local-authority-revenue-expenditure-and-financing-england-2014-to-2015-individual-local-authority-data-outturn" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/local-authority-revenue-expenditure-and-financing-england-2014-to-2015-individual-local-authority-data-outturn<br></a><br>Local authorities receive a ring-fenced public health grant from the Department for Health but physical activity is a non-prescribed public health function. Local authorities are best placed to assess and deliver the services their communities need and are locally accountable for those decisions, therefore this spending has not been formally analysed by the department.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","39636","2016-06-13T15:39:46.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523425/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523425/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523425/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-06-07","Exercise","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what proportion of all local authority spending was spent on physical activity services in the most recent period for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Liz McInnes","Heywood and Middleton","Liz McInnes","39635"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523426","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-06-14","<p>Enforcement action against unauthorised encampments is primarily a matter for local authorities, landowners and the police. The Department does not collect information centrally on the total costs of such clearances.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2016-06-14T14:56:30.123Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523426/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523426/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523426/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-06-07","Travellers: Caravan Sites","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what assessment his Department has made of the cost to the public purse of (a) eviction notices and (b) legal action related to the clearance of sites of unauthorised encampments in England in 2015.","false","Biography information for Wendy Morton","Aldridge-Brownhills","Wendy Morton","39621"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523427","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-06-13","<p>My Department has not had any civil servants based in Coventry in the last five years, or in fact since the department was created under the last Labour government.</p><p>My Department has 16 offices across England, with staff working to drive up housing supply, increase the number of home owners, boost local growth and support strong communities with excellent public services. We have 69 employees in the West Midlands in our Birmingham office.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2016-06-13T15:36:11.993Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523427/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523427/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523427/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-06-07","Department for Communities and Local Government: Coventry","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many of his Department's civil servants were based in Coventry in each of the last five years; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","39666"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523429","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-06-15","<p>Public investment in improving broadband is nearly £1.7 billion, including £790 million of UK government funding, to bring superfast broadband to areas of the UK where it would not otherwise be available. Superfast broadband is now available to 90 per cent of UK premises and this will reach 95 per cent by December 2017.</p><p> </p><p>The Government has also implemented a basic broadband scheme to enable all premises to gain access to speeds of at least 2Mbps. This allows residents to gain access to every government service available online.</p><p> </p><p>Furthermore, in November 2015 the Prime Minister announced the Government’s intention to introduce a new broadband Universal Service Obligation (USO) with the aim to provide a safety net for those homes and business in the hardest to reach parts of the UK without access to superfast broadband.</p><p> </p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2016-06-15T08:45:59.9Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523429/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523429/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523429/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-06-07","Broadband: Rural Areas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what support the Government is providing to remote rural communities on obtaining reliable access to broadband.","false","Biography information for Richard Arkless","Dumfries and Galloway","Richard  Arkless","39670"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523430","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-06-15","<p>Universal Service Providers responsible for delivering the broadband Universal Service Obligation (USO) will be designated by Ofcom following changes to primary and secondary legislation. No decision has been taken yet on funding the USO’s delivery .</p><p> </p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2016-06-15T08:46:28.847Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523430/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523430/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523430/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-06-07","Broadband","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what assistance the Government plans to provide to broadband suppliers to meet the terms of the Universal Services Obligation.","false","Biography information for Richard Arkless","Dumfries and Galloway","Richard  Arkless","39671"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523431","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-06-15","<p>The Secretary of State regularly visit all parts of the United Kingdom, including Scotland. Details of meetings with external organisations are published on a quarterly basis and can be accessed via the <a href="http://gov.uk/" target="_blank">gov.uk</a> website.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2016-06-15T16:10:03.297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523431/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523431/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523431/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-06-07","Department for Culture, Media and Sport: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how many times he has visited Scotland in an official capacity since the 2015 General Election; and what meetings were held on each such visit.","false","Biography information for Chris Law","Dundee West","Chris Law","39828"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523433","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-06-13","<p>In accordance with normal practice the independent marketing agents analysed the leading bids and bidders. Mr Firtash was regarded as a high net worth individual capable of meeting the contractual obligations.</p><p>The Ministry of Defence (MOD) took a 10% deposit (over £5 million) on exchange of contracts and later a legal charge at completion to secure payment obligations. In addition, all funds were paid to the MOD through UK regulated solicitors, in accordance with normal practice, to ensure that appropriate financial checks were made on their client.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-06-13T15:24:26.973Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523433/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523433/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523433/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-06-07","Brompton Road Station","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to the Answers of 7 April 2014 to Questions 194734 to 194737, what checks were made on the provenance of the funds used to purchase Brompton Road underground station.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","39792"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523434","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-06-13","<p>The purchaser, Dmitri Firtash made the highest bid.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-06-13T15:08:06.083Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523434/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523434/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523434/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-06-07","Brompton Road Station","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to the Answers of 7 April 2014 to Questions 194734 to 194737, who made the highest bid for Brompton Road underground station.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","39765"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523435","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-06-13","<p>I have visited Scotland six times in an official capacity since the 2015 General Election.</p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2016-06-13T15:25:01.25Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523435/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523435/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523435/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-06-07","Ministry of Defence: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many times he has visited Scotland in an official capacity since the 2015 General Election; and what meetings were held on each such visit.","false","Biography information for Chris Law","Dundee West","Chris Law","39829"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523436","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-06-13","<p>The Royal Navy currently deploys unmanned systems to enhance maritime surveillance and improve situational awareness in a number of air and sea environments.</p><p>I am withholding further information as its disclosure would, or would be likely to, prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of the Armed Forces.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-06-13T16:11:43.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523436/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523436/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523436/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-06-07","Unmanned Marine Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether the Royal Navy has deployed any unmanned maritime systems for the purpose of (a) anti-submarine and (b) port and harbour security.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","39740"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523437","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-06-14","<p>The Government takes its responsibilities for maintaining the integrity of our submarine fleet extremely seriously and dedicates considerable resource to ensuring that the credibility and standards for operational effectiveness will continue to be met. Our submarine fleet will not be rendered obsolete by new technologies, including developments in unmanned underwater vehicle technology. I am withholding further details as publication would prejudice or would be likely to prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of the Armed Forces.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","39738","2016-06-14T15:56:08.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523437/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523437/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523437/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-06-07","Unmanned Marine Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether his Department (a) has allocated and (b) plans to allocate resources to study the potential threat posed by unmanned underwater vehicles to the SSBN fleet.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","39741"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523438","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-06-13","<p>The official responsible for the sale of Brompton Road has now retired, the senior official responsible for the disposals programme has left the Department.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-06-13T15:12:54.677Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523438/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523438/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523438/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-06-07","Brompton Road Station","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to the Answers of 7 April 2014 to Questions 194734 to 194737, who the named official was who was responsible for the sale of Brompton Road underground station.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","39791"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523439","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-06-13","<p>The Department was not aware of the FBI investigation at the point of sale.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-06-13T15:11:40.007Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523439/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523439/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523439/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-06-07","Brompton Road Station","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to the Answers of 7 April 2014 to Questions 194734 to 194737, whether his Department was aware of the FBI investigation into Dmitri Firtash when it sold Brompton Road underground station.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","39788"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523440","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-06-13","<p>The independent marketing agent was Jones Lang LaSalle.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-06-13T15:12:12.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523440/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523440/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523440/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-06-07","Brompton Road Station","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to the Answers of 7 April 2014 to Questions 194734 to 194737, who the independent marketing agent was for the sale of Brompton Road underground station.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","39789"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523441","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-06-13","<p>The names of the 12 bidders cannot be released as to do so would prejudice commercial interests.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-06-13T15:23:42.02Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523441/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523441/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523441/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-06-07","Brompton Road Station","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to the Answers of 7 April 2014 to Questions 194734 to 194737, who the 12 bidders were for Brompton Road underground station.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","39790"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523442","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-06-13","<p>RAF personnel have not carried out airstrikes outside the coalition mission in the Iraq and Syria conflict zone since 2 December 2015.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-06-13T15:04:17.197Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523442/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523442/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523442/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-06-07","Middle East: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether any RAF personnel have carried out airstrikes outside the coalition mission in the Iraq and Syria conflict zone since 2 December 2015.","false","Biography information for Mr David Davis","Haltemprice and Howden","Mr David Davis","39785"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523443","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-06-13","<p>Following an extensive Assessment Phase, the Department has concluded that the GA-ASI Certified Predator B is the only platform capable of meeting the Protector Programme's Key User Requirements. Certified Predator B is a modification of the highly successful Predator B platform which incorporates a number of safety and capability enhancements.</p><p>The Demonstration Phase of the Programme, which will follow approval of the Programme's Main Gate Business Case, will subject Certified Predator B to a comprehensive Test and Evaluation Plan to demonstrate the system's ability to meet the Department's requirements for the capability through its expected in-service life.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-06-13T16:22:36.323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523443/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523443/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523443/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-06-07","Unmanned Air Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether his Department has demonstrated the capability of Certified Predator B for the duration of the Protector programme.","false","Biography information for Mr David Davis","Haltemprice and Howden","Mr David Davis","39786"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523444","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-06-13","<p>Joint Doctrine Publication (JDP) 0-30.2, Unmanned Aircraft Systems, (which will replace Joint Doctrine Note 2/11, The UK Approach to Unmanned Aircraft Systems) was endorsed by the Ministry of Defence (MOD) Joint Doctrine and Concepts Board in November 2015 with an agreed timeline for the MOD Development, Concepts and Doctrine Centre to produce it in mid-2016. On current plans JDP 0-30.2 is expected to be published in July 2016.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-06-13T15:03:46.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523444/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523444/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523444/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-06-07","Unmanned Air Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what timeline has been proposed for publication of the revised Joint Doctrinal Note on UK Unmanned Systems.","false","Biography information for Mr David Davis","Haltemprice and Howden","Mr David Davis","39787"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523445","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-06-14","<p>The Government takes its responsibilities for maintaining the integrity of our submarine fleet extremely seriously and dedicates considerable resource to ensuring that the credibility and standards for operational effectiveness will continue to be met. Our submarine fleet will not be rendered obsolete by new technologies, including developments in unmanned underwater vehicle technology. I am withholding further details as publication would prejudice or would be likely to prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of the Armed Forces.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","39741","2016-06-14T15:56:08.863Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523445/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523445/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523445/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-06-07","Unmanned Marine Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps his Department is taking to safeguard Royal Navy submarines from risks posed by underwater drones.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","39738"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523446","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-06-13","<p>Seven Puma Mk2 helicopters have been fitted with the Wire Strike Protection System. The remainder of the fleet will have the system fitted by the end of summer 2017.</p><p>The helicopter you refer to (XW229) was not fitted with the Wire Strike Protection System. The Service Inquiry into the incident is on-going and findings are yet to be published.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-06-13T16:22:01.66Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523446/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523446/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523446/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-06-07","Puma Helicopters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to the Answer of 19 April 2016 to Question 33645, how many Puma Mk2 helicopters are fitted with the Wire Strike Protection System; and whether the Puma Mk2  that crashed in Afghanistan on 11 October 2015 was fitted with such a system.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","39739"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523447","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-06-14","<p>The Government set out its assessment of the impacts of the welfare policies in the Welfare Reform and Work Act on 20<sup>th</sup> July 2015. It set out its assessment of the impacts of the social rents policies in the Act on 28<sup>th</sup> September 2015.</p><p> </p><p>A link to the impact assessments is included:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://services.parliament.uk/bills/2015-16/welfarereformandwork/documents.html" target="_blank">http://services.parliament.uk/bills/2015-16/welfarereformandwork/documents.html</a></p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","39685 ; 39686 ; 39687 ; 39688","2016-06-14T10:44:29.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523447/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523447/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523447/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-06-07","Veterans: Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment his Department has made of the effect of the Welfare Reform and Work Act 2016 on access to housing for veterans.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","39689"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523448","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-06-13","<p>UK Liaison Officers located in Saudi Headquarters exchange information between the UK and the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia to give the UK a better degree of insight into Saudi processes.</p><p>They remain under UK command and control and are not embedded with the Saudis. They do not provide training or advice on International Humanitarian Law compliance, and have no role in the Saudi targeting chain.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2016-06-13T15:22:06.85Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523448/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523448/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523448/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-06-07","Yemen: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to the Answer of 26 April 2016 to Question 35103, what the role is of the Liaison Officers deployed in Saudi coalition headquarters.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","39711"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523449","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-06-13","<p>The UK is part of a collaborative partnership on F-35 and therefore pays a shared contribution to the development of capability beyond the Block 3F capability. The cost of this activity, although provisionally estimated, has yet to be finalised with industry and is the subject of on-going discussion with the eight Partner Nations. As these costs will be the subject of commercial negotiations over the coming year, they cannot be made public at this time.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-06-13T16:20:30.79Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523449/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523449/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523449/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-06-07","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will estimate the cost of upgrading the mission software on F35B Lightning II aircraft operated by the Royal Air Force after the completion of Block 3F testing.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","39657"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523450","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-06-13","<p>As part of Coalition forces, the RAF is conducting airstrikes against Daesh targets in support of ISF operations in Fallujah.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-06-13T15:25:35.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523450/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523450/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523450/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-06-07","Iraq: Islamic State","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what support the armed forces is providing to Iraqi forces related to the conflict with Daesh in Falujah.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","39653"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523451","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-06-13","<p>Russia withdrew some close air support aircraft and associated engineering capacity earlier this year. However, around the time of their withdrawal, Russia increased its attack helicopter fleet and, therefore, our assessment is that the net effect on Russian deployed capability in Syria has been low.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-06-13T15:26:07.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523451/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523451/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523451/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-06-07","Syria: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what reports he has received on the extent of the withdrawal of Russian forces from the conflict in Syria.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","39654"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523452","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-06-14","<p>The Covenant is a promise from the nation ensuring that those who serve or who have served in the Armed Forces, and their families, are treated fairly. The Covenant is delivered by Government Departments, Local Government Authorities, the Charitable Sector and Companies.</p><p>Recent steps taken by the Ministry of Defence (MOD) include setting up a network of Armed Forces Covenant champions across the services and the launch of a new Covenant website and branding in January this year. We have been running the application process for the annual £10 million Covenant fund and the £25 million Aged Veterans Fund as well as reviewing applications for LIBOR funding. Work is also being undertaken with financial services providers to tailor their products for the Armed Forces community including Banking, Insurance and Credit History. Our engagement with Local Government Authorities to ensure that the Armed Forces Community can access the same services as other local residents has continued.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-06-14T15:55:21.713Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523452/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523452/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523452/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-06-07","Armed Forces Covenant","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what recent steps his Department has taken to adhere to the Armed Forces Covenant.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","39690"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523453","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-06-15","<p>Information on the number of UK Regular Armed Forces personnel medically discharged by Financial Year and Service since 2010 is given in the attached.</p><p> </p><p>Defence Statistics release annual updates on medical discharges in the UK Regular Armed Forces as an Official Statistic publication. The next statistical release is due in July 2016 which will present data for financial year 2015-16. The latest report for 2014-15 can be found at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/medical-discharges-among-uk-service-personnel-statistics-index" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/medical-discharges-among-uk-service-personnel-statistics-index</a></p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-06-15T14:08:22.373Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523453/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523453/answer","39645 - Table showing UK regular UK AF personnel medically discharged by FY and service since 2010.docx","39645 - Table showing UK regular UK AF personnel medically discharged by FY and service since 2010.docx","UK Regualr AF Medically Discharged","UK Regualr AF Medically Discharged","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523453/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-06-07","Armed Forces: Discharges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many service personnel were medically discharged from the (a) Royal Navy excluding the Royal Marines, (b) Royal Marines, (c) Army and (d) Royal Air Force in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Dr Julian Lewis","New Forest East","Dr Julian Lewis","39645"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523454","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-06-15","<p>This information is not held in the format requested. However, the Ministry of Defence (MOD) does hold information on the average length of time between attendance at a medical board and the date of medical discharge for UK Regular Armed Forces personnel.</p><p> </p><p>For those UK Regulars discharged between 1 April 2010 and 31 March 2015, the median averages are as follows:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Service</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Median average number of days between a medical board and subsequent medical discharge</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Royal Navy</p></td><td><p>132</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Royal Marines</p></td><td><p>133</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Army</p></td><td><p>223</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Royal Air Force</p></td><td><p>173</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Those who are medically discharged are entitled to the highest level of resettlement provision through the Career Transition Partnership (CTP), regardless of how long they have served or the nature and cause of injuries. We also offer specialised support for wounded, injured and sick personnel and those with the most complex barriers to employment to ensure they receive the most appropriate support within their recovery pathway. This is delivered through the Defence Recovery Capability and is supported by the Career Transition Partnership Assist (CTP Assist) programme. The purpose of CTP Assist is to deliver an individualised, needs-based service to those Service personnel who face the greatest barriers to employment given their medical condition.</p><p> </p><p>The MOD Veterans’ Welfare Service (VWS) provides welfare support automatically to those medically discharged, with an 'on request' service for all other members of the veterans community.</p><p> </p><p>The Transition Protocol is an established practice to ensure the effective transition of health and social care for injured Service leavers to local public providers. There is regular and close co-operation between the MOD, the Department of Health, NHS England and the Devolved Administrations in order to ensure that it is working successfully.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-06-15T14:07:35.047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523454/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523454/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523454/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-06-07","Armed Forces: Discharges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the average length is of the transition period for personnel of each of the Armed Forces between a decision of the Medical Board recommending discharge and that discharge taking place; and what support is given to personnel during that period to support the transition to civilian life.","false","Biography information for Dr Julian Lewis","New Forest East","Dr Julian Lewis","39646"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523455","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-06-15","<p>The Naval Service employs 29 Recovery Cell/Troop (NSRC) staff who have broadly equivalent responsibilities to those of Personal Recovery Officers (PROs) and oversee the recovery of Wounded, Injured and Sick (WIS) personnel. NSRC staff do not differentiate between different categories of injury; all WIS are managed equitably with their recovery pathway being directed by doctors, physiotherapists, military Departments of Community Mental Health and Occupational Therapists. Not all personnel on a recovery pathway are due to receive medical discharge; 84% return to work.</p><p> </p><p>A total of 67 PROs are based within 11 Personnel Recovery Units (PRUs) across the UK and Germany; PRUs are military units established for the command and care of WIS soldiers with the greatest need. All Army WIS personnel have a dedicated PRO assigned to them, to assist them through the recovery process and co-ordinate support from other agencies. If the individual remains in their unit the PRO will be someone in the unit who has been assigned by their Commanding Officer.</p><p> </p><p>Soldiers are transferred to a PRU if their Chain of Command or unit recommend they need more help than the unit can provide. There are a number of reasons for this, such as the nature or severity of their injury or illness, the distance between the soldier’s home address and the unit (if the soldier is at home on recovery duty), or because the unit is due to deploy. The PRUs are not residential facilities, but are organised on a regional basis allowing soldiers to be transferred to the one closest to them.</p><p> </p><p>The RAF has two full time and two part-time PROs based in the Personnel Recovery Centre at RAF High Wycombe.</p><p> </p><p>RAF PROs are responsible for supporting WIS personnel through their recovery pathway and in support of their patient care whether they are returning to Service or being medically discharged. They encourage and, where necessary, direct WIS personnel to manage their own recovery pathway as much as they are able. RAF PROs become the line manager for WIS and provide mentoring, coaching and welfare support throughout their recovery. They maintain regular contact with WIS personnel for up to six months after their discharge.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-06-15T14:11:24.347Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523455/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523455/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523455/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-06-07","Armed Forces: Discharges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the role is of personal recovery officers related to different categories of injury of armed forces personnel who are due to receive medical discharge; how many such officers there are in each branch of the Armed Forces; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Dr Julian Lewis","New Forest East","Dr Julian Lewis","39647"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523456","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-06-13","<p>The following table provides the number of UK Armed Forces personnel with a Defence Medical Services registration at a Ministry of Defence (MOD) medical practice in Scotland at various points in time since 1 July 2013:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>As at</p></td><td><p>Naval Service</p></td><td><p>Army</p></td><td><p>RAF</p></td><td><p>Total</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1 July 2013</p></td><td><p>4,170</p></td><td><p>3,840</p></td><td><p>3,080</p></td><td><p>11,080</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1 July 2014</p></td><td><p>4,190</p></td><td><p>3,790</p></td><td><p>2,580</p></td><td><p>10,560</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1 July 2015</p></td><td><p>4,260</p></td><td><p>3,410</p></td><td><p>1,190</p></td><td><p>9,650</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1 April 2016</p></td><td><p>4,820</p></td><td><p>3,890</p></td><td><p>1,920</p></td><td><p>10,640</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>It should be noted that due to rounding, subtotals by Service will not always add up to the total.</p><p> </p><p>The MOD does not hold records of all Armed Forces personnel and Veterans who are registered with an NHS medical practice in Scotland.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-06-13T15:10:25.733Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523456/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523456/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523456/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-06-07","Armed Forces: General Practitioners","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many (a) army, (b) navy and (c) RAF personnel have registered with a doctor in Scotland in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Steven Paterson","Stirling","Steven Paterson","39581"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523457","Department for Education","false","2016-06-15","<p>Computer science has been included in the science element of the English Baccalaureate (EBacc) since 2014. To enter the EBacc science pillar, pupils can enter core and additional science GCSE; enter GCSE science double award; or enter three single sciences at GCSE. The single sciences are biology, chemistry, computer science and physics.</p><p> </p><p>A time series of the total number of entries in GCSE computer science for the last three years is published as part of the “Revised GCSE and equivalent results in England: 2014 to 2015 (revised)” statistical first release (SFR).[1]</p><p> </p><p>[1] <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/502685/SFR01_2016_Subject_Timeseries.xls" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/502685/SFR01_2016_Subject_Timeseries.xls</a> (“Subject time series tables: SFR01/2016” document)</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2016-06-15T14:14:18.007Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523457/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523457/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523457/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-06-07","ICT: English Baccalaureate","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what estimate she has made of the number of students who have taken up computer science as an option in the EBacc in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Michelle Donelan","Chippenham","Michelle Donelan","39573"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523458","Department for Education","false","2016-06-13","<p>Pursuant to the Answer of 23 May 2016 to Question 37487, the Education Funding Agency has directed academies to admit pupils 12 times between April 2012 and April 2016.</p><p> </p><p>The Office of the Schools Adjudicator (OSA) does not issue directions in relation to maintained schools but will determine the case if a school which a local authority is seeking to direct refers the case on to the adjudicator.</p><p> </p><p>Prior to 2007, directions under section 96 and 97 of the School Standards and Framework Act 1998 (SSFA) were determined by the Secretary of State. The Education and Inspections Act 2006 amended the SSFA to bring powers to the OSA to determine appeals.</p><p> </p><p>The table below shows the number of directions upheld in each year from 2007 to 2010.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>LA directions upheld by OSA</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2007</p></td><td><p>6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2008</p></td><td><p>20</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2009</p></td><td><p>9</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>7</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2016-06-13T16:50:33.1Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523458/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523458/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523458/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-06-07","Academies: Admissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 23 May 2016 to Question 37487, whether the Education Funding Agency has directed academies to admit pupils 10 or 12 times since 2012; and how many directions sought by local authorities and referred on to the Schools Adjudicator were upheld in each year from 2005 to 2010.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","39593"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523459","Department for Education","false","2016-06-15","<p>The Department does not retain a central record of the land holding arrangements for individual academies. However, the vast majority of academies will be occupying sites on the basis of a lease from the relevant local authority.</p><p>No school gains the freehold of a school site as a result of becoming an academy. Academies own their own land only where the school already owned the land before converting to academy status. These are usually former foundation or voluntary schools which are generally the freeholders of their own land even as maintained schools and in the case of voluntary schools which tend to mainly occupy land which was not originally provided by the state.</p><p>The Department does not have detailed information on the current and historic ownership of academy land and buildings, and had chosen not to prioritise the expenditure necessary to resolve the issue.</p><p> </p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson",,"2016-06-15T08:51:05.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523459/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523459/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523459/answer","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523459/answer/previousversion/3491","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523459/answer/previousversion/3491",,,"60","Education","Education","2016-06-07","Academies: Freehold","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many academy schools hold the freehold of their school sites.","false","Biography information for Jess Phillips","Birmingham, Yardley","Jess Phillips","39667"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523460","Department for Education","false","2016-06-15","<p>We currently have no plans to carry out religious literacy training in the Department.</p><p> </p><p>Civil Service Learning, the main training portal for Civil Servants, has a broad range of diversity and inclusion courses, which are available to all civil servants. There is also a two day course covering both Abrahamic and Dharmic religions for officials who need a more in depth understanding to carry out their role.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2016-06-15T14:11:28.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523460/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523460/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523460/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-06-07","Department for Education: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will take steps to ensure that staff in her Department receive religious literacy training.","false","Biography information for Fiona Bruce","Congleton","Fiona Bruce","39676"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523461","Department for Education","false","2016-06-13","<p>Information in the form requested is not readily available and could be compiled only at a disproportionate cost.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2016-06-13T16:51:07.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523461/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523461/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523461/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-06-07","Department for Education: Domestic Visits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how much her Department spent on travel and accommodation for civil servants accompanying the Minister of State for Schools on official business since July 2014.","false","Biography information for Jess Phillips","Birmingham, Yardley","Jess Phillips","39668"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523462","Department for Education","false","2016-06-13","<p>Local authorities have contacted the Education Funding Agency 88 times asking it to intervene on the Secretary of State’s behalf in academy admissions.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Financial Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Requests received from local authorities</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>April 2012 - March 2013</p></td><td><p>24</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>April 2013 - March 2014</p></td><td><p>28</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>April 2014 - March 2015</p></td><td><p>36</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>8</strong><strong>8</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2016-06-13T16:51:48.767Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523462/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523462/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523462/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-06-07","Academies: Admissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 24 May 2016 to Question 37615, on academies: admissions, how many times local authorities asked her to intervene in each year from 2012 to 2015.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","39597"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523463","Department for Education","false","2016-06-13","<p>Since 2012, the Secretary of State visited Birmingham Children’s Services Department in September 2013.</p><p> </p><p>Since 2012, the Minister of State for Children and Families visited Birmingham Children’s Services Department in December 2013.</p><p> </p><p>Since her appointment in September 2013, the Chief Social Worker for Children and Families visited Birmingham Children’s Services Department in December 2013 (with the Minister of State for Children and Families), and in January 2014 and July 2014.</p><p> </p><p>The Secretary of State and the Parliamentary Under Secretary of State for Schools have also met officials from Birmingham City Council in London.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson",,"2016-06-13T15:31:10.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523463/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523463/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523463/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-06-07","Social Services: Birmingham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, on what occasions (a) she, (b) Ministers of her Department and (c) the Chief Social Worker for Children have visited Birmingham Children's Services Department since 2012.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","39857"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523464","Department for Education","false","2016-06-15","<p>My Rt Hon Friend, the Secretary of State for Education, visited Scotland in December 2015 for a number of engagements.</p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2016-06-15T14:12:17.873Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523464/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523464/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523464/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-06-07","Department for Education: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many times she has visited Scotland in an official capacity since the 2015 General Election; and what meetings were held on each such visit.","false","Biography information for Chris Law","Dundee West","Chris Law","39830"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523465","Department for Education","false","2016-06-13","<p>We are currently investigating institutions that may be operating as unregistered independent schools in England, as referred to by Her Majesty’s Chief Inspector Sir Michael Wilshaw in his recently published letter. We will make a statement about progress in due course.</p><p>It is important to recognise that new settings come to our attention and existing ones close, or are confirmed not to be operating as schools on a regular basis.</p><p>Sir Michael Wilshaw’s published letter can be accessed on GOV.UK at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/unregistered-schools-ofsted-advice-note" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/unregistered-schools-ofsted-advice-note</a></p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","40028","2016-06-13T15:27:44.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523465/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523465/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523465/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-06-07","Out-of-school Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will estimate the number of unregistered schools in England.","false","Biography information for Jess Phillips","Birmingham, Yardley","Jess Phillips","39845"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523466","Department for Education","false","2016-06-14","<p>Building Bulletin 100 advises on fire safety design for new school buildings and includes a fire risk assessment within its suite of guidance. This risk assessment is not intended to be part of a data collection exercise and therefore the Department does not hold the information requested.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","39768","2016-06-14T16:28:58.04Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523466/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523466/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523466/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-06-07","Schools: Fire Extinguishers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, with reference to the Education Funding Agency guidance, Building Bulletin 100: Design for fire safety in schools, published on 11 March 2014, how many schools that scored high or medium on the risk assessment have not been fitted with sprinklers.","false","Biography information for Lyn Brown","West Ham","Lyn Brown","39767"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523467","Department for Education","false","2016-06-14","<p>Building Bulletin 100 advises on fire safety design for new school buildings and includes a fire risk assessment within its suite of guidance. This risk assessment is not intended to be part of a data collection exercise and therefore the Department does not hold the information requested.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","39767","2016-06-14T16:28:58.103Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523467/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523467/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523467/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-06-07","Schools: Fire Prevention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, with reference to the Education Funding Agency guidance, Building Bulletin 100: Design for fire safety in schools, published on 11 March 2014, how many schools with pupils with Special Educational Needs have scored (a) high, (b) medium and (c) low on the fire risk assessment.","false","Biography information for Lyn Brown","West Ham","Lyn Brown","39768"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523468","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-06-14","<p>I visited Scotland in May 2016 for the inauguration of the Shetland Gas Plant, and again in June 2016 to attend the Oil and Gas Industry Conference. Details of meetings with external organisations will be published in due course at <a href="http://www.gov.uk/" target="_blank">www.gov.uk</a>.</p>","Hastings and Rye","Amber Rudd",,"2016-06-14T15:56:02.48Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523468/answer","Biography information for Amber Rudd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523468/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523468/answer",,,,,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-06-07","Department for Energy and Climate Change: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, how many times she has visited Scotland in an official capacity since the 2015 General Election; and what meetings were held on each such visit.","false","Biography information for Chris Law","Dundee West","Chris Law","39831"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523469","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-06-14","<p>This Government remains firmly committed to the Climate Change Act, and to meeting our climate change target of an at least 80% emissions reduction by 2050. We are clear that this must be done while keeping our energy supply secure and low cost.</p><p> </p><p>Discussions on the fifth carbon budget (2028-2032) are continuing and we will make an announcement as soon as possible.</p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2016-06-14T13:49:34.977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523469/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523469/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523469/answer",,,,,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-06-07","Greenhouse Gas Emissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, if she will make it her policy for the UK to reduce its actual greenhouse gas emissions by 61 per cent below 1990 levels by 2030.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","39703"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523470","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-06-13","<p>In 2014/15 over 2.1m households received £140 off their electricity bills as a result of the Warm Home Discount.</p><p> </p><p>Under the Industry Initiatives element of the scheme nearly 28,000 households received an average of £548 debt assistance with their energy bills in 2014/15.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2016-06-13T16:13:05.833Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523470/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523470/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523470/answer",,,,,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-06-07","Warm Home Discount Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, if she will estimate the average reduction in electricity bills in Great Britain for households in receipt of the Warm Home Discount Scheme.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Mr Nigel Dodds","39696"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523471","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-06-13","<p>During the recent public consultation on the Warm Home Discount Scheme, there were six responses asking for the scheme to be extended to Northern Ireland.</p><p> </p><p>We will publish the response to the consultation as soon as we can.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2016-06-13T16:11:56.583Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523471/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523471/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523471/answer",,,,,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-06-07","Warm Home Discount Scheme: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what recent representations she has received on the extension of the Warm Home Discount Scheme to Northern Ireland.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Mr Nigel Dodds","39691"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523472","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-06-13","<p>From 2011 to 2015, energy suppliers spent a total of £868m on electricity bill rebates under the Core and Broader Group elements of the Warm Home Discount. The annual breakdown is set out below.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong><em>Scheme year</em></strong></p></td><td><p><strong><em>Total contribution on rebates</em></strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Scheme year 1 ( 2011/2012)</p></td><td><p>£112.3m</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Scheme Year 2 (2012/2013)</p></td><td><p>£198.1m</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Scheme Year 3 (2013/2014)</p></td><td><p>£248.66m</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Scheme Year 4 (2014/2015)</p></td><td><p>£309.3m</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>We expect that at least £286m has been spent by suppliers on direct rebates in 2015/16.</p><p> </p><p>From 2011 to 2015, households have also received other assistance through the Warm Home Discount to the value of £264m.</p><p> </p><p>Government announced in the Spending Review in November 2015 that the Warm Home Discount scheme would be extended to 2020/21 at current levels of £320m per year, rising with inflation, to help households who are at risk of fuel poverty with their energy bills.</p><p> </p><p>Further details can be found in Ofgem’s annual reports at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.ofgem.gov.uk/publications-and-updates/warm-home-discount-annual-report-scheme-year-4" target="_blank">https://www.ofgem.gov.uk/publications-and-updates/warm-home-discount-annual-report-scheme-year-4</a>.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2016-06-13T16:12:14.803Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523472/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523472/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523472/answer",,,,,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-06-07","Warm Home Discount Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, how much has been contributed by energy suppliers towards the rebate on electricity bills under the Warm Home Discount Scheme in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Mr Nigel Dodds","39692"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523473","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-06-13","<p>The extension of the Warm Home Discount Scheme to Northern Ireland was debated in Parliament on 2 March 2015. A transcript of the debate is at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201415/cmhansrd/cm150302/debtext/150302-0004.htm" target="_blank">http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201415/cmhansrd/cm150302/debtext/150302-0004.htm</a></p><p> </p><p>DECC officials continue to discuss fuel poverty issues with officials in the Northern Ireland Executive.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2016-06-13T16:12:44.013Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523473/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523473/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523473/answer",,,,,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-06-07","Warm Home Discount Scheme: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what discussion she has had with the Northern Ireland Executive on the possible extension of the Warm Home Discount Scheme to Northern Ireland.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Mr Nigel Dodds","39693"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523474","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-06-16","<p>The Government has no plans to move to China the design and manufacture of specialised steel casks used in the transport of nuclear fuels in relation to the sites for which it is responsible.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2016-06-16T15:46:46.947Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523474/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523474/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523474/answer",,,,,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-06-07","Nuclear Fuels: China","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what plans the Government has to move the design and manufacture of specialised steel casks used to store nuclear fuels during transport to China.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Monaghan","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Dr Paul Monaghan","39623"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523475","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-06-14","<p>This is a matter for individual companies.</p><p> </p><p>The Department has not had any representations from individual companies on their plans for coal stockpiling.</p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2016-06-14T13:50:10.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523475/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523475/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523475/answer",,,,,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-06-07","Coal","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, whether she has received representations in the last 12 months on coal that has been or will be stockpiled in the UK.","false","Biography information for Clive Lewis","Norwich South","Clive Lewis","39570"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523476","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-06-14","<p>DECC publishes data on coal stocks held in the UK. The table below shows the stocks held at the end of the last 10 years. This includes stocks held at electricity generators, ports and undistributed stocks held at coal mines.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>UK Coal Stocks at end of year (thousand tonnes)</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><em>2006</em></p></td><td><p>17,210</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><em>2007</em></p></td><td><p>14,155</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><em>2008</em></p></td><td><p>17,246</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><em>2009</em></p></td><td><p>24,091</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><em>2010</em></p></td><td><p>16,885</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><em>2011</em></p></td><td><p>16,041</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><em>2012</em></p></td><td><p>13,003</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><em>2013</em></p></td><td><p>14,287</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><em>2014</em></p></td><td><p>18,641</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><em>2015 (provisional)</em></p></td><td><p>14,500</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p><em>Source: Energy Trends Table 2.6, March 2016 available at:</em></p><p><em><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/solid-fuels-and-derived-gases-section-2-energy-trends" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/solid-fuels-and-derived-gases-section-2-energy-trends</a></em></p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2016-06-14T13:51:35.753Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523476/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523476/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523476/answer",,,,,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-06-07","Coal","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what estimate she has made of the level of coal stockpiling in the UK in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Clive Lewis","Norwich South","Clive Lewis","39571"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523477","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-06-14","<p>The Department has not made an assessment of the potential levels of UK coal exports in each of the next five years.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2016-06-14T13:52:19.02Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523477/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523477/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523477/answer",,,,,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-06-07","Coal: Exports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what estimate her Department has made of potential levels of UK coal exports in each of the next five years.","false","Biography information for Clive Lewis","Norwich South","Clive Lewis","39572"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523478","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-06-14","<p>Natural England has part funded the production of book called <em>Designing for Biodiversity: A Technical Guide for New and Existing Buildings.</em> The publication includes detailed advice on provision for swifts (as well as a range of other species) in new developments, which local authorities may find useful.</p><p> </p><p>No specific guidance has been issued to local authorities on the conservation of nestling swifts in the demolition or renovation of old housing estates.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2016-06-14T11:34:22.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523478/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523478/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523478/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-06-07","Birds: Conservation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether her Department has issued guidance to local authorities on the conservation of nestling swifts in the demolition or renovation of old housing estates.","false","Biography information for Michelle Donelan","Chippenham","Michelle Donelan","39574"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523479","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-06-13","<p>Defra submitted evidence to the European Commission in April 2015 to inform their review of the EU Nature Directives. A Commission delegation then visited the UK in June 2015 to discuss the Directives in greater detail with Government officials, business group representatives and environmental non-governmental organisations. I spoke at EU Environment Council in December 2015 in support of improving how the Nature Directives are implemented and to make clear that the UK didn’t wish to see the Directives renegotiated. Defra’s written evidence and a recording of the December Council meeting are available on the European Commission website.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2016-06-13T09:57:12.7Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523479/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523479/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523479/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-06-07","Nature Conservation: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what representations her Department has made to the European Commission on the proposed reform of the EU Nature Directive.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","39643"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523480","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-06-15","<p>The Animal and Plant Health Agency issued export health certificates for 235 consignments of dogs to be exported to Hong Kong during 2015, relating to 267 dogs in total.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2016-06-15T16:47:34.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523480/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523480/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523480/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-06-07","Dogs: Exports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many consignments of dogs were exported from the UK to Hong Kong in 2015; and how many dogs were in each such consignment.","false","Biography information for Angela Smith","Penistone and Stocksbridge","Angela Smith","39701"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523481","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-06-14","<p>The Secretary of State has visited Scotland on two separate occasions since the 2015 General Election and met:</p><p>Diageo</p><p>Scotch Whisky Association</p><p>Scotland Food and Drink</p><p>NFU Scotland</p><p>Quality Meat Scotland</p><p>Ian Duncan MEP</p><p>Ruth Davidson MSP</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2016-06-14T10:23:14.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523481/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523481/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523481/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-06-07","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many times she has visited Scotland in an official capacity since the 2015 General Election; and what meetings were held on each such visit.","false","Biography information for Chris Law","Dundee West","Chris Law","39832"
