ficial capacity since the 2015 General Election; and what meetings were held on each such visit.","false","Biography information for Chris Law","Dundee West","Chris Law","39835"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523594","Department for International Development","false","2016-06-14","<p>The UK has increased its bilateral spend on water and sanitation year on year since 2004, from £31.2million (2004/05) to £180.8million (2014/15).</p><p>The Department for International Development does not allocate a set proportion of the aid budget to water and sanitation. The UK Aid strategy commits the UK to helping at least 60million people get access to water and sanitation by 2020. We will allocate the resources required to achieve this to the relevant programmes.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2016-06-14T15:47:55.98Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523594/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523594/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523594/answer",,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-06-07","Developing Countries: Sanitation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, if she will increase her Department's expenditure on water and sanitation.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","39812"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523595","Department for International Development","false","2016-06-13","<p>The UK more than doubled its humanitarian commitment to Yemen in 2015-16 to £85 million, making us the fourth largest donor last year. We have so far helped more than 1.3 million Yemenis who have been affected by the conflict. Over the next twelve months, we will continue to work with a range of partners to address the widespread humanitarian needs across Yemen, as well as helping to de-escalate the conflict, improve commercial and humanitarian access, lay the groundwork for recovery and push for a sustainable political solution. Budgets for 2016/17 will be announced in due course.</p>","New Forest West","Sir Desmond Swayne",,"2016-06-13T16:31:46.61Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523595/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523595/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523595/answer",,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-06-07","Yemen: Overseas Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what humanitarian support and assistance her Department plans to provide to aid agencies in Yemen in each of the next 12 months; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","39846"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523596","Ministry of Justice","true","2016-09-30","<p>Well-run prisons are fundamental to the proper functioning of our justice system, and a vital part of our reform plans. Private providers play an important role in the prison estate. Performance of all providers is closely monitored and we will not hesitate to take action where standards fall short.</p><p> </p><p>All private prisons are managed by a full-time, on-site controller. Where a provider fails to meet the expected level of performance, financial remedies can be applied. This ensures that providers are incentivised to properly support the rehabilitation of offenders through a safe, decent and secure regime.</p><p> </p><p>The attached table provides a breakdown of financial remedies applied for both HMP Birmingham and HMP Oakwood (HMP Featherstone II was the working name during construction of HMP Oakwood).</p><p> </p><p>No financial remedies were applied at either prison in 2011/12. Operation of HMP Birmingham transferred from HM Prison Service to G4S Justice Services in October 2011. HMP Oakwood opened in April 2012.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2016-09-30T09:17:39.417Z","2016-10-05T10:02:36.853Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523596/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523596/answer","39844 & 39594 Birmingham & Oakwood Finanical Remedies.xlsx","39844 & 39594 Birmingham & Oakwood Finanical Remedies.xlsx","Birmingham & Oakwood Financial Remedies","Birmingham & Oakwood Financial Remedies","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523596/answer","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523596/answer/previousversion/12785","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523596/answer/previousversion/12785",,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-06-07","Birmingham Prison","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how much was levied in respect of financial remedies in each key performance indicator designated in respect of the contractual agreement between his Department and G4S Care and Justice Services (UK) Limited at HM Prison Birmingham in each year since 2011.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","39844"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523597","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-06-13","<p>The information requested could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2016-06-13T12:43:10.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523597/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523597/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523597/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-06-07","Ministry of Justice: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how much has been levied in respect of financial remedies in each key performance indicator designated in respect of the contractual agreement entitled the Provision of Total Facilities Management between his Department and (a) Amey Community Ltd, (b) Carillion (AMBS) Ltd, (c) EMCOR Facilities Services Ltd, (d) Enterprise Managed Services Ltd, (e) G4S Integrated Services (UK) Ltd, (f) Mitie Facilities Services Ltd and (g) Sodexo Ltd in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","39843"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523598","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-06-14","<p>Details of all ministerial meetings are published at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/moj-gifts-hospitality-travel-and-meetings" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/moj-gifts-hospitality-travel-and-meetings</a>.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2016-06-14T13:48:52.37Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523598/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523598/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523598/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-06-07","Ministry of Justice: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many times he has visited Scotland in an official capacity since the 2015 General Election; and what meetings were held on each such visit.","false","Biography information for Chris Law","Dundee West","Chris Law","39836"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523599","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-06-15","<p>The Government is determined to crack down on the compensation culture and has announced reforms, including raising the small claims limit, to tackle the problem. These reforms will build on previous measures taken by the MoJ to control costs, tackle fraud, strengthen the medical evidence process and reduce incentives to pursue trivial whiplash claims. £5,000 is considered to be the appropriate level for the small claims limit and the rationale for this will be set out in the consultation document which will be published in due course.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2016-06-15T15:02:45.073Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523599/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523599/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523599/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-06-07","Small Claims","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, for what reason the Government is proposing to raise the small claims limit to £5000 rather than to £3000.","false","Biography information for Julian Sturdy","York Outer","Julian Sturdy","39716"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523600","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-06-14","<p>The number of offenders found guilty at all courts in England and Wales, from 1986 to 2015, can be viewed in the table. The figures from 2005 onwards are a further breakdown of data published in the outcomes by offences data tool in the annual Criminal Justice Statistics publication, at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/criminal-justice-system-statistics-quarterly-december-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/criminal-justice-system-statistics-quarterly-december-2015</a></p><p> </p><p>Information as to whether each case referred to abortion or miscarriage Is not available.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","39728 ; 39729 ; 39730 ; 39732","2016-06-14T15:29:56.967Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523600/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523600/answer","39728 - 39729 - 39730 - 39731 - 39732 - Table.xls","39728 - 39729 - 39730 - 39731 - 39732 - Table.xls","Offences against the person act 1861 Section 58/59","Offences against the person act 1861 Section 58/59","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523600/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-06-07","Abortion: Convictions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many people have been convicted of the offence of child destruction under the Infant Life Preservation Act 1929 for performing abortions on themselves or causing their own miscarriage in each year since 1986; and what each such case was.","false","Biography information for Fiona Bruce","Congleton","Fiona Bruce","39731"
