"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523607","Cabinet Office","false","2016-06-14","<p>All government departments have record keeping systems in place, and The National Archives regularly conducts and publishes information management assessments of departments.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-06-14T08:48:51.313Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523607/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523607/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523607/answer",,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-06-07","Child Abuse in North Wales Judicial Inquiry Review","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, with reference to recommendation 2 on page 250 of the Report of the Macur Review, published in March 2016, what steps his Department is taking to ensure that all government departments possess an accurate database of the documents and materials held by them.","false","Biography information for Ann Clwyd","Cynon Valley","Ann Clwyd","39737"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523608","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-06-14","<p>As the then Secretary of State for Wales said in his statement to the House on 17 March, the police and the Crown Prosecution Service are aware of the specifics of this matter and it is for them to consider further.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","39735","2016-06-14T12:57:10.05Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523608/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523608/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523608/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-06-07","Child Abuse in North Wales Judicial Inquiry Review","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, with reference to recommendation 5 on page 251 of the Report of the Macur Review, published in March 2016, what assessment he has made of the potential merits of a police investigation to consider whether there is sufficient evidence and public interest relating to matters of malfeasance in public office in the Welsh Office in relation to the abuse of children in care in North Wales.","false","Biography information for Ann Clwyd","Cynon Valley","Ann Clwyd","39736"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523609","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-06-14","<p>As the then Secretary of State for Wales said in his statement to the House on 17 March, the police and the Crown Prosecution Service are aware of the specifics of this matter and it is for them to consider further.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","39736","2016-06-14T12:57:09.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523609/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523609/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523609/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-06-07","Child Abuse in North Wales Judicial Inquiry Review","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, with reference to recommendation 5 on page 251 of the Report of the Macur Review, published in March 2016, what assessment he has made of the potential merits of a police investigation to consider whether there is sufficient evidence and public interest relating to matters of malfeasance in public office or perverting the course of justice in North West Wales Police in relation to the abuse of children in care in North Wales.","false","Biography information for Ann Clwyd","Cynon Valley","Ann Clwyd","39735"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523610","Ministry of Justice","true","2016-09-30","<p>Well-run prisons are fundamental to the proper functioning of our justice system, and a vital part of our reform plans. Private providers play an important role in the prison estate. Performance of all providers is closely monitored and we will not hesitate to take action where standards fall short.</p><p> </p><p>All private prisons are managed by a full-time, on-site controller. Where a provider fails to meet the expected level of performance, financial remedies can be applied. This ensures that providers are incentivised to properly support the rehabilitation of offenders through a safe, decent and secure regime.</p><p> </p><p>The attached table provides a breakdown of financial remedies applied for both HMP Birmingham and HMP Oakwood (HMP Featherstone II was the working name during construction of HMP Oakwood).</p><p> </p><p>No financial remedies were applied at either prison in 2011/12. Operation of HMP Birmingham transferred from HM Prison Service to G4S Justice Services in October 2011. HMP Oakwood opened in April 2012.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2016-09-30T09:17:40.667Z","2016-10-05T10:02:47.723Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523610/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523610/answer","39844 & 39594 Birmingham & Oakwood Finanical Remedies.xlsx","39844 & 39594 Birmingham & Oakwood Finanical Remedies.xlsx","Birmingham & Oakwood Financial Remedies","Birmingham & Oakwood Financial Remedies","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523610/answer","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523610/answer/previousversion/12786","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523610/answer/previousversion/12786",,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-06-07","Featherstone Prison","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how much has been levied in financial remedies relating to each key performance indicator in the contractual agreement between his Department and HM Prison Featherstone II in each year since 2011.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","39594"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523611","Leader of the House","false","2016-06-15","<p>I have not visited Scotland in an official capacity since the 2015 General Election.</p>","Epsom and Ewell","Chris Grayling",,"2016-06-15T14:54:12.677Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523611/answer","Biography information for Chris Grayling","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523611/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523611/answer",,,,,,,,"34","Leader of the House","Leader of the House","2016-06-07","Leader of the House of Commons: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Leader of the House, how many times he has visited Scotland in an official capacity since the 2015 General Election; and what meetings were held on each such visit.","false","Biography information for Chris Law","Dundee West","Chris Law","39837"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523612","Northern Ireland Office","false","2016-06-14","<p>The UK’s 2014-20 allocation for Structural Funds was 5 per cent less than for the 2007-13 period. The Government therefore allocated the UK's nations an equivalent 5 per cent less for 2014-20 than in the previous period. Northern Ireland’s allocation for 2014-20 is €513.4m.</p><p> </p><p>The post-2020 Multiannual Financial Framework has not been proposed.</p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers","39806","2016-06-14T14:49:33.343Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523612/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523612/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523612/answer",,,,,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2016-06-07","EU Grants and Loans: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what change there was in the amount the EU Commission proposed to make available in structural funds to Northern Ireland for the period 2014 to 2020 from the period 2007 to 2013; what steps her Department took to limit such change; and if she will estimate the level of such funding that Northern Ireland will be allocated after 2020.","false","Biography information for Karl McCartney","Lincoln","Karl McCartney","39807"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523613","Northern Ireland Office","false","2016-06-14","<p>The UK’s 2014-20 allocation for Structural Funds was 5 per cent less than for the 2007-13 period. The Government therefore allocated the UK's nations an equivalent 5 per cent less for 2014-20 than in the previous period. Northern Ireland’s allocation for 2014-20 is €513.4m.</p><p> </p><p>The post-2020 Multiannual Financial Framework has not been proposed.</p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers","39807","2016-06-14T14:49:33.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523613/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523613/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523613/answer",,,,,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2016-06-07","EU Grants and Loans: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, if she will estimate the amount of structural funding that the EU Commission will allocate to Northern Ireland in the post-2020 Multiannual Financial Framework.","false","Biography information for Karl McCartney","Lincoln","Karl McCartney","39806"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523614","Northern Ireland Office","false","2016-06-14","<p>The Government believes that the UK is stronger, safer and better off in a reformed EU.</p><p>The Northern Ireland Office has not undertaken any work in preparation for the possibility of a vote to leave the EU.</p><p> </p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace",,"2016-06-14T14:53:41.18Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523614/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523614/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523614/answer",,,,,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2016-06-07","UK Membership of EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what preliminary work her Department has carried out in preparation for the possibility of a vote to leave the EU.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Mr Nigel Dodds","39695"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523615","Northern Ireland Office","false","2016-06-13","<p>I am in regular contact with Irish ministers on security and other matters. Political and operational co-operation is strong and the Irish authorities are having considerable success disrupting the activities of dissident republican terrorists and bringing them to justice.</p><p> </p><p>I commend the PSNI and AGS for their work on tackling the terrorist threat and their efforts to keep people safe on both sides of the border. The establishment of the Joint Agency Task Force on organised crime adds another important dimension to this already effective co-operation.</p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers",,"2016-06-13T14:33:05.03Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523615/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523615/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523615/answer",,,,,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2016-06-07","Terrorism: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what discussions she has had with her Irish Republic counterpart on security co-operation since the latest published security assessment of the threat posed by Irish republican terrorists.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Mr Nigel Dodds","39698"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523616","Prime Minister","false","2016-06-13","<p>I regularly visit all parts of the United Kingdom, including Scotland. Details of my meetings with external organisations are published on a quarterly basis and can be accessed via the gov.uk website.</p><p> </p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron",,"2016-06-13T16:53:16.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523616/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523616/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523616/answer",,,,,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2016-06-07","Prime Minister: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, how many times he has visited Scotland in an official capacity since the 2015 General Election; and what meetings were held on each such visit.","false","Biography information for Chris Law","Dundee West","Chris Law","39838"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523617","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-06-13","<p>To date the Departmental spend to convert one Voyager aircraft's cabin into an enhanced configuration is £8.9 million out of a total estimated cost of £9.6 million.</p><p>The aircraft's primary role will continue to be aircraft refuelling.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-06-13T16:25:45.283Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523617/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523617/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523617/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-06-07","Military Aircraft: Ministers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what recent estimate the Government has made of the cost to the public purse to date of the adaptation of the Voyager aircraft for the transport of senior ministers.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","39746"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523618","Scotland Office","false","2016-06-15","<p>The post-2020 Multi Annual Financial Framework has not been proposed. I refer the hon Member to a letter signed by the former Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, the Rt hon Vince Cable of 17th April 2014, on ‘European Regional Development Fund and European Social Fund: UK Allocations 2014 to 2020’. This is available at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/307492/bis-14-772-uk-allocations-eu-structural-funds-2014-2020-letter.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/307492/bis-14-772-uk-allocations-eu-structural-funds-2014-2020-letter.pdf</a>.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2016-06-15T12:01:12.603Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523618/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523618/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523618/answer",,,,,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2016-06-07","EU Grants and Loans: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, if he will estimate the level of structural funding that the EU Commission's formula will allocate to Scotland in the post-2020 Multi Annual Financial Framework.","false","Biography information for Karl McCartney","Lincoln","Karl McCartney","39802"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523619","Scotland Office","false","2016-06-13","<p>I am frequently in Scotland for a range of meetings, events and official engagements. Details of meetings with external organisations are published in quarterly returns which are available at gov.uk.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2016-06-13T14:39:23.89Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523619/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523619/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523619/answer",,,,,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2016-06-07","Scotland Office: Domestic Visits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, how many times he has visited Scotland in an official capacity since the 2015 General Election; and what meetings were held on each such visit.","false","Biography information for Chris Law","Dundee West","Chris Law","39839"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523620","Scotland Office","false","2016-06-15","<p>I refer the hon Member to the information provided at HM Treasury analysis: the long-term economic impact of EU membership and the alternatives (paragraphs 1.113 – 1.126). This is available at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/517415/treasury_analysis_economic_impact_of_eu_membership_web.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/517415/treasury_analysis_economic_impact_of_eu_membership_web.pdf</a>.</p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2016-06-15T12:02:23.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523620/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523620/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523620/answer",,,,,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2016-06-07","EU Grants and Loans: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what change there was in the amount the EU Commission proposed to make available in structural funds to Scotland for the period 2014 to 2020 from the period 2007 to 2013; and what steps his Department took to limit such change; and what estimate he has made of the level of such funding for Scotland after 2020.","false","Biography information for Karl McCartney","Lincoln","Karl McCartney","39808"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523621","Wales Office","false","2016-06-14","<p>I refer my hon Friend to the letter signed by the then Secretary of State for Business Innovation and Skills, Vince Cable MP, on ‘European Regional Development Fund and European Social Fund: UK allocations 2014-2020’.</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/307492/bis-14-772-uk-allocations-eu-structural-funds-2014-2020-letter.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/307492/bis-14-772-uk-allocations-eu-structural-funds-2014-2020-letter.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p>The post-2020 Multiannual Financial Framework has not been proposed.</p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns","39809 ; 39811","2016-06-14T14:41:56.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523621/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523621/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523621/answer",,,,,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2016-06-07","EU Grants and Loans: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what change there was in the amount the EU Commission proposed to make available in structural funds to Wales for the period 2014 to 2020 from the period 2007 to 2013; what steps his Department took to limit such a change; and if he will estimate the amount of such funding made available to Wales after 2020.","false","Biography information for Karl McCartney","Lincoln","Karl McCartney","39825"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523622","Department for Transport","false","2016-06-14","<p>Transport in Scotland is in large part a devolved matter. However, the Secretary of State has met members of the Scottish Parliament in London and other Department for Transport ministers have visited Scotland on the following dates:</p><p> </p><p>Robert Goodwill 5 November 2015 and 21 March 2016</p><p>Claire Perry 8 January 2016</p><p>Andrew Jones 7 September 2016</p><p> </p><p>The visits included meetings on a variety of transport-related issues.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-06-14T13:01:12.947Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523622/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523622/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523622/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-07","Department for Transport: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many times he has visited Scotland in an official capacity since the 2015 General Election; and what meetings were held on each such visit.","false","Biography information for Chris Law","Dundee West","Chris Law","39840"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523623","Department for Transport","false","2016-06-13","<p>In response to the Environmental Noise (England) Regulations 2006, the Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs provided noise maps for transport sources such as roads, which identify noise ‘Important Areas’, the most seriously affected locations. Those which are located next to the trunk road and motorway network in England are required to be investigated by Highways England.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>Between the A41 near Apex Corner and M1 junction 2 in the Mill Hill area, four locations on the M1 have been identified as being noise ‘Important Areas’. Highways England are continuing investigations into these sites, including a study at a location opposite Mill Hill Broadway station to see if a noise barrier is practical here, which is expected to be completed by March 2017.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-06-13T13:19:41.19Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523623/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523623/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523623/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-07","M1: Barnet","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will make an assessment of the level of vehicular noise on the M1 passing Mill Hill town.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","39796"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523624","Department for Transport","false","2016-06-13","<p>Govia Thameslink Railway’s (GTR’s) provision of services for the Thameslink, Southern and Great Northern franchise only began on 14 September 2014, with Southern services included from 26 July 2015.</p><p> </p><p>There is an incentive/penalty regime in place and this has seen just over £2 million levied against GTR in respect of their Cancellation and Short-Formation performance benchmarks.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2016-06-13T16:37:17.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523624/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523624/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523624/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-07","Govia Thameslink Railway: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how much has been paid in fines by Govia Thamelink Railway to his Department to compensate for poor performance in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","39858"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523625","Department for Transport","false","2016-06-13","<p>Govia Thameslink Railway’s (GTR's) provision of services for the Thameslink, Southern and Great Northern franchise only began on 14 September 2014, with Southern services included from 26 July 2015.</p><p>Network Rail’s performance is regulated by the Office of Rail and Road (ORR), who have agreed a £4.1m package of improvements to be delivered by Network Rail on the Southern part of GTR franchise area in order to address performance issues.</p><p>There is a compensation and incentive regime element within the Track Access Agreement between Network Rail and each operator, and this is overseen by the ORR.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2016-06-13T16:56:27.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523625/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523625/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523625/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-07","Govia Thameslink Railway","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how much has been paid in fines by Network Rail to Govia Thamelink Railway to  compensate for poor performance in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","39871"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523626","Department for Transport","false","2016-06-13","<p>The Department for Transport has made no recent assessment of the merits of planting noise barriers with vegetation alongside motorways and trunk roads.</p><p> </p><p>Guidance on the design of noise barriers, which includes vegetated barriers, is contained within the Design Manual for Roads and Bridges:</p><p><a href="http://www.standardsforhighways.co.uk/ha/standards/DMRB/vol10/section5.htm" target="_blank">http://www.standardsforhighways.co.uk/ha/standards/DMRB/vol10/section5.htm</a></p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-06-13T13:04:47.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523626/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523626/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523626/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-07","Roads: Noise","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment his Department has made of the merits of planting noise barriers with vegetation alongside motorways and trunk roads.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","39710"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523627","Department for Transport","false","2016-06-14","<p>The Department for Transport and South Yorkshire Passenger Transport Executive, the joint funders of the tram train pilot project, have been advised that Network Rail has initiated a review of the current programme of works needed to adapt their infrastructure to operate the tram train vehicles between Meadowhall South and Rotherham Parkgate.</p><p> </p><p>The Department understands that Network Rail has encountered significant issues with the approval of new bespoke electrification equipment needed to operate the tram train vehicles. The joint funders are clearly disappointed by this further delay.</p><p> </p><p>The current programme showed delivery of these works by early spring 2017, however until the outcome of the Network Rail review is known, no further details can be provided.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","39700","2016-06-14T10:07:23.047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523627/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523627/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523627/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-07","Sheffield Supertram","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, for what reasons the Sheffield to Rotherham tram-train scheme has been delayed.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","39699"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523628","Department for Transport","false","2016-06-14","<p>The Department for Transport and South Yorkshire Passenger Transport Executive, the joint funders of the tram train pilot project, have been advised that Network Rail has initiated a review of the current programme of works needed to adapt their infrastructure to operate the tram train vehicles between Meadowhall South and Rotherham Parkgate.</p><p> </p><p>The Department understands that Network Rail has encountered significant issues with the approval of new bespoke electrification equipment needed to operate the tram train vehicles. The joint funders are clearly disappointed by this further delay.</p><p> </p><p>The current programme showed delivery of these works by early spring 2017, however until the outcome of the Network Rail review is known, no further details can be provided.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","39699","2016-06-14T10:07:23.117Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523628/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523628/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523628/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-07","Sheffield Supertram","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent discussions he has had with Network Rail on delays to the Sheffield to Rotherham tram-train scheme.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","39700"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523629","Department for Transport","false","2016-06-13","<p>On the M1 between the A41 near Apex Corner and M1 junction 2 in the Mill Hill area, four areas are identified by the Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs noise mapping process as being noise ‘Important Areas’ which require further investigation.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>One of these areas is located along the M1 southbound carriageway from the beginning of Station Road to Woodland Way, opposite Mill Hill Broadway station and is currently being studied to see if a noise barrier is practical here. There are a number of issues to be investigated, including whether a barrier can be put in place over a structure and along an embankment.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-06-13T13:16:03.867Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523629/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523629/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523629/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-07","M1: Barnet","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment his Department has made of the potential merits of installing a continuous noise barrier on the eastern side of the M1 passing through Mill Hill.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","39709"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523630","Department for Transport","false","2016-06-14","<p>Cycle tracks, where provided, offer cyclists an alternative to cycling in the carriageway. However, the decision to use a lane or not will depend on the individual. We have no plans to make to make the use of lanes mandatory.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-06-14T09:03:34.093Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523630/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523630/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523630/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-07","Cycleways","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps he is taking to encourage more cyclists to use cycle lanes rather than cycling on the main highway; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Greg Knight","East Yorkshire","Sir Greg Knight","39600"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523631","Department for Transport","false","2016-06-14","<p>Highways England is developing road schemes at several locations to help reduce congestion on the M25 including:</p><p> </p><ul><li>Upgrade of the M25 between junction 10 (A3) and junction 16 (M40) to a smart motorway, with start of construction before the end of 2019/20.</li><li>A far reaching study to look into the south-west quadrant of the M25 to address the increasing demand on this section.</li><li>An upgrade of junctions 10, 25 and 28 to have started construction by the end of 2019/20.</li></ul><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-06-14T09:07:52.447Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523631/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523631/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523631/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-07","M25: Road Traffic","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what plans he has to reduce congestion on the M25 motorway; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Greg Knight","East Yorkshire","Sir Greg Knight","39601"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523632","Department for Transport","false","2016-06-14","<p>Highways England has carefully planned the roadworks on the M1 to ensure that works are carried out as concurrently as possible. This is to reduce the impact on motorists wherever possible, whilst delivering increasing levels of investment to improve the motorway network and enable economic growth.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-06-14T09:32:03.563Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523632/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523632/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523632/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-07","M1: Speed Limits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, for what reasons the imposition of 50mph average speed limits on three stretches of M1 motorway, one in Northamptonshire and two in Leicestershire, were carried out consecutively rather than concurrently to avoid delays for motorists; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Greg Knight","East Yorkshire","Sir Greg Knight","39602"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523633","Department for Transport","false","2016-06-14","<p>Our assessment of the registration of bicycles indicates it would require a licensing process similar to that for cars and motorcycles. As there are in excess of 20 million bicycles in Great Britain and many change hands through second hand sales, keeping track of this would be difficult and expensive. The costs of its administration would far outweigh the revenue received and indeed any benefits received from it.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-06-14T12:11:40.95Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523633/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523633/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523633/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-07","Bicycles: Registration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the potential merits of registering bicycles with the DVLA.","false","Biography information for Michelle Donelan","Chippenham","Michelle Donelan","39576"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523634","Department for Transport","false","2016-06-13","<p>The minimum age for driving tests were last reviewed in 2010 following a widespread public consultation in 2009 on changes to the driver licensing and testing regime. The possible changes included amongst others, minimum ages, medical requirements, driving licence security and driving test vehicle requirements. The Government currently has no plans to alter minimum ages.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-06-13T14:15:11.63Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523634/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523634/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523634/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-07","Driving Tests: Age","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when the age requirements for the driving test were last reviewed.","false","Biography information for Michelle Donelan","Chippenham","Michelle Donelan","39577"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523635","Department for Transport","false","2016-06-13","<p>The Trade Union that represents Highways England Traffic Officers was consulted throughout the life of the enhanced carriageway clearance project, which focused on carriageway clearance of vehicles of all types. Trade Union representatives attended a number of meetings and specific workshops.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-06-13T12:31:34.6Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523635/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523635/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523635/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-07","Large Goods Vehicles: Accidents","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what discussions his Department has had with trades unions officials representing Highways England traffic officers on the potential danger of serious injury or death arising from trying to move a heavy goods vehicle from a live lane using a Highways England traffic officer 4 by 4 vehicle.","false","Biography information for Robert Flello","Stoke-on-Trent South","Robert Flello","39584"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523636","Department for Transport","false","2016-06-13","<p>Highways England has not received any claims relating to heavy goods vehicles damaged as a result of being moved by Highways England traffic officers in the last 12 months. Hence, no compensation has been paid.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-06-13T12:28:13.72Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523636/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523636/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523636/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-07","Large Goods Vehicles: Accidents","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how much compensation has been paid from the public purse to owners of heavy goods vehicles damaged as a result of being moved by Highways England traffic officers from live lanes to (a) hard shoulders and (b) emergency refuge areas in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Robert Flello","Stoke-on-Trent South","Robert Flello","39585"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523637","Department for Transport","false","2016-06-13","<p>Highways England does not specifically record how many Highways England traffic officers have moved heavy goods vehicles from live lanes to hard shoulders or emergency refuge areas.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-06-13T12:20:51.51Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523637/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523637/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523637/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-07","Large Goods Vehicles: Accidents","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many Highways England traffic officers have moved heavy goods vehicles from live lanes to (a) hard shoulders and (b) emergency refuge areas in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Robert Flello","Stoke-on-Trent South","Robert Flello","39586"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523638","Department for Transport","false","2016-06-13","<p>As at 6 June 2016, 910 Highways England Traffic Officers have been trained in the activity of carriageway clearance. This training is appropriate for all vehicle types as it is designed to provide specific criteria which Traffic Officers must follow to determine whether it is safe to remove any vehicle from a carriageway to a place of relative safety.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, all Traffic Officers who work on smart motorway sections are trained in the specifics of that operational environment before they are designated as safe to operate. No operational activity is undertaken by Highways England Traffic Officers without appropriate training and supporting safe systems of work.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-06-13T12:24:47.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523638/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523638/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523638/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-07","Large Goods Vehicles: Accidents","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many Highways England traffic officers have been (a) trained to move heavy goods vehicles from live motorway lanes on Smart motorways to emergency refuge areas and (b) not so trained but issued with an instruction manual to move such vehicles.","false","Biography information for Robert Flello","Stoke-on-Trent South","Robert Flello","39587"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523639","Department for Transport","false","2016-06-13","<p>The revised industry fuel standard for petrol (EN228), agreed and published by the British Standards Institution in 2013, allows up to ten per cent bioethanol content (known as ‘E10’). However, E10 is not yet on general sale in the UK and whether to supply it is a commercial decision for suppliers.</p><p> </p><p>The Transport Energy Task Force, made up of experts from industry and environmental NGOs, reported its findings to the Department for Transport in March 2015. The report, which included recommendations relating to E10, is available on the Low Carbon Vehicle Partnership’s website at:</p><p><a href="http://www.lowcvp.org.uk/projects/transport-energy-task-force.htm" target="_blank">http://www.lowcvp.org.uk/projects/transport-energy-task-force.htm</a></p><p> </p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-06-13T14:09:46.69Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523639/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523639/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523639/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-07","Biofuels","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will commission a study into the potential merits of the use of E10 petrol.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","39640"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523640","Department for Transport","false","2016-06-13","<p>A copy will be placed in the libraries of both Houses.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2016-06-13T16:46:52.467Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523640/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523640/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523640/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-07","Thameslink, Southern and Great Northern Rail Franchise","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will place in the Library a copy of his Department's Thameslink, Southern and Great Northern contractual breach notice, dated 7 July 2015.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","39629"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523641","Department for Transport","false","2016-06-14","<p>We are undertaking the biggest investment in roads in a generation to deliver better journeys for motorists. Highways England’s top priority is maintaining the safety of all motorists and road workers whilst keeping disruption to a minimum.</p><p> </p><p>Highways England, as a general principle, aim to reduce the lengths of roadworks to a maximum of 10 miles, shorter if possible and if safety allows.</p><p> </p><p>They will also be carrying out trials to raise the speed limit through roadworks to 55mph where it is safe to do so in order to help minimise queues.</p><p> </p><p>These changes could come into effect on many new schemes from 2017 depending on the outcome of the trials.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-06-14T09:44:11.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523641/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523641/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523641/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-07","Motorways: Repairs and Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what progress he has made on his plans to limit motorway roadworks to no more than stretches of two miles.","false","Biography information for Sir Greg Knight","East Yorkshire","Sir Greg Knight","39617"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523642","Department for Transport","false","2016-06-13","<p>The “Enforcement Policy: Rail Franchise Agreements and Closures” sets out what actions can be taken; a copy of this is attached, and a copy will be placed in the libraries of both Houses.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2016-06-13T16:41:28.033Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523642/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523642/answer","165902 - Enforcement Policy.pdf","165902 - Enforcement Policy.pdf","Enforcement Policy Document","Enforcement Policy Document","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523642/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-07","Thameslink, Southern and Great Northern Rail Franchise","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what penalties he is able to levy on the Thameslink, Southern and Great Northern franchisee if the terms of that franchise are breached or its performance is judged to be inadequate; and whether any such penalties have been imposed since that franchise commenced.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","39626"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523643","Department for Transport","false","2016-06-13","<p>No final decisions have yet been taken on the Crossrail 2 route. We have safeguarded a route from Angel to Hackney Central, which could form an eastern branch of Crossrail 2 at a later phase of the project, should there be a good business case and funding available for it. However, this is not being assessed as part of the core scheme under current consideration.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-06-13T14:42:16.87Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523643/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523643/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523643/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-07","Crossrail 2 Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps he is taking to assess the case for the proposed Crossrail 2 Eastern Phase.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","39611"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523644","Department for Transport","false","2016-06-13","<p>Whether to use single- or double-decker buses must be an operational decision for local bus operators. They are in the best position to understand and appreciate which type of vehicle to use on their bus routes, at which times during the day.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is committed to helping local bus operators to operate more environmentally friendly buses. Measures such as the Green Bus Fund, awarded £89m from 2009-2014 for over 1200 low emission buses, including both single and double-decker buses. The £30m Low Emission Bus Scheme, announced last year, is available to fund both single- and double-decker low emission buses and supporting infrastructure.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-06-13T12:44:47.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523644/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523644/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523644/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-07","Bus Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will make an assessment of the potential environmental and safety benefits of using single rather than double-decker buses during off-peak times on journeys with small numbers of passengers.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","39673"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523645","Department for Transport","false","2016-06-13","<p>Taxis and private hire vehicles require insurance that covers their use for hire and reward activity. Driving without valid insurance is an offence, for which penalties, including fines and points on a licence, are ultimately a matter for the courts. Drivers for and cars used by Uber and other private hire companies must meet the requirements that are set by their local licensing authority in order to operate.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-06-13T12:59:29.447Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523645/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523645/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523645/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-07","Taxis: Insurance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps his Department is taking to ensure that cars and drivers for (a) Uber and (b) other private hire companies are adequately insured.","false","Biography information for Thangam Debbonaire","Bristol West","Thangam Debbonaire","39658"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523646","Department for Transport","false","2016-06-14","<p>As the independent aviation safety regulator, the Civil Aviation Authority (CAA), only records information on flights above a certain weight threshold.</p><p> </p><p>The CAA data below includes the number of departures and arrivals on both AS332 SUPER PUMA and EUROCOPTER EC225 (H225) aircraft operated between UK airports and Oil Rigs in each year since 2007.</p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p><strong>2007</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2008</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2009</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2010</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2011</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2012</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2015</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>AS332</p></td><td><p>38200</p></td><td><p>29855</p></td><td><p>23360</p></td><td><p>18269</p></td><td><p>16614</p></td><td><p>15867</p></td><td><p>19960</p></td><td><p>10551</p></td><td><p>2866</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>EC225</p></td><td><p>7785</p></td><td><p>10238</p></td><td><p>12008</p></td><td><p>14942</p></td><td><p>18154</p></td><td><p>14191</p></td><td><p>1183</p></td><td><p>12458</p></td><td><p>15418</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-06-14T10:01:34.753Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523646/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523646/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523646/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-07","Offshore Industry: Helicopters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many and what proportion of flights in the UK North Sea oil and gas sector were undertaken by (a) Airbus EC225 and (b) AS332 helicopters airframes in each year since 2007-08.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","39766"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523647","Department for Transport","false","2016-06-13","<p>Network Rail has closed almost 1,000 level crossings since 2009 and the Department is supporting its on-going risk reduction programme through a dedicated £99 million fund during 2014-19 to secure further improvements.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2016-06-13T16:36:15.49Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523647/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523647/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523647/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-07","Level Crossings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 26 May 2016 to Question 37816, on level crossings, what his Department's expenditure on the level crossing reform programme was in the last Parliament; and how much such expenditure is budgeted in the current Parliament.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","39849"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523648","Department for Transport","false","2016-06-13","<p>The estimated cost to the public purse for preparing and publishing the</p><p> </p><p>a) Bowe Report published on 25 November 2015 was £1,500, associated with type setting and printing; and</p><p>b) Consultation on the Hendy Report, published January 2016 was zero.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2016-06-13T16:33:01.417Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523648/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523648/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523648/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-07","Network Rail","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the estimated cost to the public purse was of preparing and publishing the (a) Bowe Report into the planning of Network Rail's enhancements programme published on 25 November 2015 and (b) Hendy Report on Replanning Network Rail's Investment programme, published January 2016.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","39848"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523649","Department for Transport","false","2016-06-13","<p>The Department last published forecasts of road traffic in 2015 <a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/publications/road-traffic-forecasts-2015" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/publications/road-traffic-forecasts-2015</a>. Estimates of future trips by mode in the format set out in UIN 214853 were not in this publication but are set out below for one of our five forecast scenarios (scenario 1)</p><p> </p><p>Average Trips per person annually by mode (GB, RTF15 Scenario 1)</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Annual trips</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Walk</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Cycle</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Car Driver</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Car Passenger</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Bus</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Rail</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2015</strong></p></td><td><p>307.0</p></td><td><p>22.1</p></td><td><p>453.4</p></td><td><p>228.1</p></td><td><p>84.9</p></td><td><p>24.4</p></td><td><p>1,119.9</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2020</strong></p></td><td><p>302.3</p></td><td><p>21.1</p></td><td><p>468.3</p></td><td><p>223.7</p></td><td><p>79.3</p></td><td><p>23.9</p></td><td><p>1,118.5</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2025</strong></p></td><td><p>298.2</p></td><td><p>20.1</p></td><td><p>483.1</p></td><td><p>219.5</p></td><td><p>73.3</p></td><td><p>23.2</p></td><td><p>1,117.4</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2030</strong></p></td><td><p>296.1</p></td><td><p>20.0</p></td><td><p>488.2</p></td><td><p>216.4</p></td><td><p>71.5</p></td><td><p>23.7</p></td><td><p>1,115.9</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2035</strong></p></td><td><p>291.7</p></td><td><p>20.6</p></td><td><p>497.0</p></td><td><p>215.0</p></td><td><p>67.0</p></td><td><p>23.5</p></td><td><p>1,114.8</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2040</strong></p></td><td><p>290.4</p></td><td><p>20.5</p></td><td><p>503.9</p></td><td><p>213.8</p></td><td><p>64.8</p></td><td><p>24.1</p></td><td><p>1,117.5</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Average length of trips by mode (GB, RTF15 Scenario 1)</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>miles </strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Walk</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Cycle</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Car Driver</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Car Passenger</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Bus</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Rail</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2015</strong></p></td><td><p>0.8</p></td><td><p>2.5</p></td><td><p>9.0</p></td><td><p>10.0</p></td><td><p>7.8</p></td><td><p>24.6</p></td><td><p>7.1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2020</strong></p></td><td><p>0.8</p></td><td><p>2.4</p></td><td><p>9.1</p></td><td><p>10.0</p></td><td><p>7.9</p></td><td><p>24.5</p></td><td><p>7.2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2025</strong></p></td><td><p>0.8</p></td><td><p>2.3</p></td><td><p>9.2</p></td><td><p>10.1</p></td><td><p>8.1</p></td><td><p>24.5</p></td><td><p>7.2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2030</strong></p></td><td><p>0.8</p></td><td><p>2.3</p></td><td><p>9.2</p></td><td><p>10.1</p></td><td><p>8.1</p></td><td><p>24.6</p></td><td><p>7.3</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2035</strong></p></td><td><p>0.8</p></td><td><p>2.2</p></td><td><p>9.2</p></td><td><p>10.1</p></td><td><p>8.3</p></td><td><p>24.5</p></td><td><p>7.3</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2040</strong></p></td><td><p>0.8</p></td><td><p>2.2</p></td><td><p>9.2</p></td><td><p>10.1</p></td><td><p>8.6</p></td><td><p>24.7</p></td><td><p>7.3</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Notes on the tables:</p><ul><li>These are for personal trips based on main mode of travel. The National Transport Model (NTM) does not produce mode information for different stages of the same trip.</li><li>These estimates are based on scenario 1 in the Road Traffic Forecasts 2015 (see <a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/publications/road-traffic-forecasts-2015" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/publications/road-traffic-forecasts-2015</a>).</li><li>Figures are for Great Britain and so cannot be directly compared to published National Travel Survey statistics on average trips and trip lengths by mode, which are for England only.</li><li>The estimated number of walking trips is higher than latest National Travel Survey statistics. This is due to the estimates being based on older NTS data when walking trips were at a higher level. Forecasts for car travel are calibrated to actual traffic statistics so are not considered to be affected by this variance.</li><li>The forecasts do not account for the Departments Cycling and Walking Investment Strategy, which was still in development when these forecasts were estimated.</li><li>There were five scenarios published in RTF15. Scenario 1 has been presented here for consistency with the methodology used in the answer to UIN 214853. The other scenarios are based on alternative forecasting assumptions and will produce different forecast numbers of trips.</li><li>The NTM road traffic forecasts are based on our understanding of the way people make travel choices, the expected path of the key drivers and travel behaviour at the time the forecast is made and assume no change in government policy beyond that already announced.</li><li>Estimates of future trips and trip lengths by modes other than car travel are calculated solely for the purpose of forecasting traffic, and are not used as forecasts by the Department for policy or appraisal purposes.</li><li>The NTM is not the Department’s primary forecasting tool for rail. The forecasts will not match with rail forecasts the Department has published elsewhere.</li><li>The National Transport Model is being updated to incorporate latest data on travel behaviour, including on mode of travel and distances travelled.</li></ul>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-06-13T12:37:53.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523649/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523649/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523649/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-07","Travel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, with reference to the Answer of 24 November 2014 to Question 214853, on travel, whether his Department has produced an updated National Transport Model estimate of future (a) annual trips by mode per person and (b) average length of trips by mode.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","39847"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523650","Department for Transport","false","2016-06-13","<p>The possibility of bringing forward the planned improvement to this route was fully explored with Arriva Rail North during the closing phases of the franchising process in late 2015 and was not considered achievable. This position has currently not changed, but should it do so then earlier implementation would then be considered with the franchisee.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-06-13T14:30:52.693Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523650/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523650/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523650/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-07","Railways: North Yorkshire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will make an assessment of the potential merits of bringing forward planned improvements to the Northern Rail service between Scarborough and York that are due to take place in 2019.","false","Biography information for Kevin Hollinrake","Thirsk and Malton","Kevin Hollinrake","39769"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523651","Wales Office","false","2016-06-14","<p>No. Lady Justice Macur specifically cautioned Ministers against publishing certain groups of names, for example to protect against prejudicing pending and ongoing criminal investigations and prosecutions.</p><p> </p><p>An unredacted version of the report has been provided to the Independent Inquiry into Child Sexual Abuse, chaired by Justice Lowell Goddard, and was seen by representatives from Operations Pallial, Hydrant and Orarian.</p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns",,"2016-06-14T14:45:58.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523651/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523651/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523651/answer",,,,,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2016-06-07","Child Abuse in North Wales Judicial Inquiry Review","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, if he will place in the library an unredacted copy of Lady Macur's review of the Tribunal of Inquiry into the abuse of children in North Wales.","false","Biography information for Ann Clwyd","Cynon Valley","Ann Clwyd","39624"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523652","Wales Office","false","2016-06-14","<p>I refer my hon Friend to the letter signed by the then Secretary of State for Business Innovation and Skills, Vince Cable MP, on ‘European Regional Development Fund and European Social Fund: UK allocations 2014-2020’.</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/307492/bis-14-772-uk-allocations-eu-structural-funds-2014-2020-letter.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/307492/bis-14-772-uk-allocations-eu-structural-funds-2014-2020-letter.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p>The post-2020 Multiannual Financial Framework has not been proposed.</p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns","39809 ; 39825","2016-06-14T14:41:56.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523652/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523652/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523652/answer",,,,,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2016-06-07","EU Grants and Loans: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what change there was in the amount of funding the EU Commission made available in structural funds to (a) Wales and (b) the Valleys for the period 2014 to 2020 from the period 2007 to 2014; what steps his Department took to limit such change; and if he will estimate the level of such funding that Wales will be allocated after 2020.","false","Biography information for Karl McCartney","Lincoln","Karl McCartney","39811"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523653","Wales Office","false","2016-06-14","<p>I refer my hon Friend to the letter signed by the then Secretary of State for Business Innovation and Skills, Vince Cable MP, on ‘European Regional Development Fund and European Social Fund: UK allocations 2014-2020’.</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/307492/bis-14-772-uk-allocations-eu-structural-funds-2014-2020-letter.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/307492/bis-14-772-uk-allocations-eu-structural-funds-2014-2020-letter.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p>The post-2020 Multiannual Financial Framework has not been proposed.</p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns","39811 ; 39825","2016-06-14T14:41:56.443Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523653/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523653/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523653/answer",,,,,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2016-06-07","EU Grants and Loans: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, if he will estimate the level of structural funding that the EU Commission will allocate to (a) Wales and (b) the Valleys in the post-2020 Multiannual Financial Framework.","false","Biography information for Karl McCartney","Lincoln","Karl McCartney","39809"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523654","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-06-13","<p>The information you have requested is not available.</p><p> </p><p>The decision as to whether a paper-based review is appropriate is made by the Healthcare Professional. Their decision on whether to do so is based on evidence provided by the claimant to support their claim including all medical evidence from the claimant’s GP, hospital doctor or other appropriate clinicians.</p><p> </p>","Witham","Priti Patel","39674","2016-06-13T10:31:10.41Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523654/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523654/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523654/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-06-07","Employment and Support Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people who have claimed employment and support allowance after a paper-based review were refused a paper-based review upon re-assessment for that allowance in each year since 2009-10.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","39660"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523655","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-06-09","<p>The Government has a clear position which has remained the same for around 70 years and we have no plans to change this policy: UK State Pensions are payable worldwide and are uprated abroad where we have a legal requirement to do so, for example in the European Economic Area or countries where we have a reciprocal agreement that allows for uprating. Annual increases are paid to UK state pension recipients in Bermuda and in Gibraltar.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2016-06-09T12:24:40.79Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523655/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523655/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523655/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-06-07","State Retirement Pensions: British Overseas Territories","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what progress he has made on implementing the request by the governments of British Overseas Territories during the December 2015 Joint Ministerial Council on establishing parity of treatment between all British Overseas Territories on the uprating of pensions for UK state pension holders residing in those territories.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","39650"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523656","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-06-13","<p>The information you have requested is not available.</p><p> </p><p>The decision as to whether a paper-based review is appropriate is made by the Healthcare Professional. Their decision on whether to do so is based on evidence provided by the claimant to support their claim including all medical evidence from the claimant’s GP, hospital doctor or other appropriate clinicians.</p><p> </p>","Witham","Priti Patel","39660","2016-06-13T10:31:10.477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523656/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523656/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523656/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-06-07","Employment and Support Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many requests for paper-based reviews for employment and support allowance were submitted in each year since 2009-10; and how many of those claims were (a) accepted and (b) rejected.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","39674"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523657","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-06-13","<p>The department routinely collects management information on the descriptors awarded to each claimant when they have a PIP assessment.</p><p> </p><p>In the PIP assessment, individuals are assessed on their ability to complete a number of key every day activities (for example, relating to the ability to dress and undress). Within each activity there are a number of descriptors, each representing a varying level of ability to carry out the activity. A descriptor may indicate the need to use an aid or appliance.</p><p> </p><p>Data on the claimant’s primary disabling condition is recorded for those individuals who have a PIP assessment. Claimants may often have multiple disabling conditions upon which their decision is based, but only the primary condition is recorded.</p><p> </p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2016-06-13T13:02:38.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523657/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523657/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523657/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-06-07","Personal Independence Payment: Arthritis","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps his Department plans to take to collect data on the number of people with arthritis who qualify for personal independence payments on the basis of their need to use aids and appliances.","false","Biography information for Liz McInnes","Heywood and Middleton","Liz McInnes","39637"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523658","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-06-13","<p>Access to Work continues to support deaf people and people with hearing loss. Access to Work has specialist teams including a dedicated team for deaf people and those with hearing loss to help customers and their employers with advice on adjustments, technological support and personal budgets which are currently being trialled.</p><p> </p><p>The number of people in general helped by Access to Work has grown in each of the three years to 2014/15 and are published quarterly here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/514468/access-to-work-statistics-to-dec-2015.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/514468/access-to-work-statistics-to-dec-2015.pdf</a></p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2016-06-13T15:29:23.613Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523658/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523658/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523658/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-06-07","Access to Work Programme: Hearing Impairment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what recent assessment he has made of the effectiveness of the Access to Work programme for young deaf people; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","39610"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523659","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-06-13","<p>I refer the Rt. Hon. Member to the answer I gave on 24 May 2016 to Question <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2016-05-19/37593" target="_blank">37593</a></p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2016-06-13T10:50:17.56Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523659/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523659/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523659/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-06-07","Health and Safety Executive: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of the potential effect of reductions in funding for the Health and Safety Executive in the period to 2019-20 on occupational health and safety; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","39615"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523660","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-06-13","<p>For claimants with Arthritis who were awarded the Daily Living component of Personal Independence Payment between April 2013 and October 2015, 52% gained all of their points from Aids and Appliances.</p><p> </p><p>The source of the data is the PIP computer system. This is unpublished data and, as such, it does not meet the quality standard required for official statistics publication. It should be used with caution and it may be subject to future revision.</p><p> </p><p>Data is based on primary disabling condition as recorded on the PIP computer system. Claimants may often have multiple disabling conditions upon which the decision is based but only the primary condition is shown in these statistics.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2016-06-13T10:52:34.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523660/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523660/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523660/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-06-07","Personal Independence Payment: Arthritis","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what proportion of people who qualify for personal independence payments on the basis of their need of use of aids and appliances have arthritis.","false","Biography information for Liz McInnes","Heywood and Middleton","Liz McInnes","39634"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523661","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-06-14","<p>The Secretary of State for Work and Pensions and his Ministerial team are working closely with their Scottish Government counterparts. The Secretary of State will be visiting Scotland shortly, and also attending the Joint Ministerial Working Group on Welfare.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2016-06-14T16:08:21.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523661/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523661/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523661/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-06-07","Department for Work and Pensions: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many times he has visited Scotland in an official capacity since the 2015 General Election; and what meetings were held on each such visit.","false","Biography information for Chris Law","Dundee West","Chris Law","39842"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523662","Department for Transport","false","2016-06-14","<p>The UK’s independent safety regulator, the Civil Aviation Authority (CAA) takes seriously concerns raised in the safe operation of commercial helicopter transport.</p><p> </p><p>The CAA currently leads the Offshore Helicopter Safety Action Group (OHSAG) which seeks to drive through safety improvements.</p><p> </p><p>The Group is represented across industry and includes pilot and workforce representatives from key organisations to facilitate dialogue between helicopter operators, workforce representatives, manufacturers and regulators.</p><p> </p><p>The OHSAG has made significant safety improvements, including prohibiting helicopter flights in the most severe sea conditions.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-06-14T10:17:58.71Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523662/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523662/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523662/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-07","Offshore Industry: Helicopters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will make an assessment of workforce confidence in the safe operation of commercial helicopter transport in the North Sea oil and gas industry.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","39826"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523663","Department for Transport","false","2016-06-14","<p>The UK Civil Aviation Authority (CAA) has been working very closely with the Norwegian CAA following the Airbus EC225LP incident on the 29<sup>th</sup> April.</p><p> </p><p>Shortly after the accident, the CAA introduced restrictions to Airbus Helicopters EC225LP to prevent operations for commercial flights by UK operators. On 11<sup>th</sup> of May, these restrictions were extended to include the AS332L2 Super Puma helicopter.</p><p> </p><p>Following a report by Norwegian Air Accident Investigators on 1st June, the CAA further extended these restrictions to prohibit all flights by these helicopters until further information is available.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-06-14T10:14:08.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523663/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523663/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523663/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-07","Offshore Industry: Helicopters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many and what proportion of (a) Airbus EC225 and (b) AS332 helicopters have been withdrawn from commercial service in the UK North Sea oil and gas sector since the fatal incident off the coast of Bergen, Norway on 29 April 2016.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","39822"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523664","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-06-14","<p>The Department for Work and Pensions (as well as the Office for National Statistics) publishes a wide range of information looking at the income distribution. We have announced we will be producing a new publication, Income Dynamics in February/March 2017, which will look at income mobility, including a measure of persistent low income, based on new data from the Understanding Society survey.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2016-06-14T14:46:57.293Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523664/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523664/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523664/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-06-07","Personal Income","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps he has taken to increase the range of statistics that his Department collects on income mobility.","false","Biography information for Adam Afriyie","Windsor","Adam Afriyie","39725"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523665","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-06-14","<p>The Government set out its assessment of the impacts of the welfare policies in the Welfare Reform and Work Act on 20<sup>th</sup> July 2015. It set out its assessment of the impacts of the social rents policies in the Act on 28<sup>th</sup> September 2015.</p><p> </p><p>A link to the impact assessments is included:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://services.parliament.uk/bills/2015-16/welfarereformandwork/documents.html" target="_blank">http://services.parliament.uk/bills/2015-16/welfarereformandwork/documents.html</a></p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","39685 ; 39686 ; 39687 ; 39689","2016-06-14T10:44:29.023Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523665/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523665/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523665/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-06-07","Young Offenders: Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment his Department has made of the effect of the Welfare Reform and Work Act 2016 on access to housing for post-release young offenders.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","39688"
